Below is a job advertisement. Perform the following tasks in the order listed below: 
- Extract the raw context of the job advertisement.
- Extract hard and soft skills from the job advertisement.
- Validate skill results by checking for 'both' skill type.
- Extract the requirements mentioned in the advertisement.
- Extract the responsibilities mentioned in the advertisement. 
- Perform G-Eval for 'Correctness' extracted the extracted results. 

[job advertisement]
Readify helps organizations innovate with technology by providing high value software and digital services. Since 2001, Readify has a strong record of helping customers in a range of industries to develop and support innovative software projects. We use agile principles and practices to form autonomous, collaborative and cross-functional teams with our customers. Readify embraces open source software, both as consumers and producers, and offer a generous paid professional development scheme. 
The Role
As a Senior Software Developer you'll provide our clients with an extremely high level of technical expertise and represent Readify as a technical expert in the wider community. You'll have the chance to make an impact in the development of complex, disruptive solutions for a wide range of organizations.
You will be able to apply your passion for technology and problem solving, using the latest, cutting edge technologies whilst working alongside and learning from talented, knowledgeable and experienced software development consultants. 
You will have the opportunity to shape the way that companies deliver software and to work with people who believe in routinely shipping quality software to production. You will need the humility to listen to customers and learn from your peers. 
This is a great role for someone who is self-motivated and loves seeing clients excited about solutions to their business problems. As a consulting organization, there may be the opportunity to travel interstate and collaborate with your interstate colleagues.
The Responsibilities
* Design, develop, test and deliver custom software solutions 
* Directly collaborate with clients on a daily basis
* Form part of an elite delivery team. They will support you and you will be expected to support them. 
Desired Skills and Experience
More than any other skill, we value a willingness to learn and a positive attitude. You'll need to be able to adapt to a wide range of technologies in this role, but we'll support you every step of the way. We expect strong communication skills, deep experience with both front-end and server-side development, and experience with agile software development. We don’t require specific framework or language experience, however we expect candidates to have an interest in skilling up in the .Net stack if they haven’t yet.

We expect you’ll have used 
some
of the following technologies and frameworks to deliver complete solutions:

Javascript / Typescript

React / Angular / Vue

WebPack

HTML5 and CSS3 (Bootstrap, Bulma, etc)

Testing frameworks (Karma, Jasmine, Mocha, Jest etc)

Continuous Integration (CI) / Continuous Delivery (CD) techniques

Strong experience with a server side programming language (C#, Go, Java, Ruby, Python, Rust, Kotlin, F#, Node etc)

Experience with Agile delivery methods

For bonus points, you may also have hands-on experience with the following:

Apache Cordova / React Native / Xamarin

DevOps and Cloud services using AWS / Azure (ARM, CloudFormation)

Experience consulting

Benefits

Work with some of the best, most well-known minds in software development

Less time in meetings, more time shipping

20 days / year of Paid Professional Development

Profit Share Scheme

Mobile, internet and software allowance

$4,200 toolkit allowance renewed every 2 years

Purchased annual leave scheme

[job advertisement]
Are you looking to join a thriving business that will reward your hard work whilst you make a difference to Children’s lives?
The Role:
We are looking for someone to focus purely on recruiting Permanent staff in the Early Childhood Educaton Sector. The role will include:
Building relationships with range of existing and prospective clients
Identify their issues and help provide the solution
Attending client visits and understanding client requirements
Representing Pulse Child Care Crew as an ambassador at career fairs and other external events
Managing recruitment processes to deliver monthly targets
Developing and executing your own candidate development strategy
Coordinating resources to ensure all vacancies are properly worked

The Benefits
Competitive salary and commission structure, with uncapped earning potential.
Have your experience and successes recognised as a key player of the business. Everyone is heard and encouraged to offer opinions.
Regular Incentives including all-expenses trips and team building days out.
Financial rewards and celebratory meals, all of which you are eligible for from Day 1.
We have a Quarterly Lunch Clubs with all-expenses paid Friday afternoon off to a posh restaurant.
Be part of a socially active and supportive team with a great balance of competitive hard work and plenty of fun.
Investors in People with a consistent focus on support through our established career development pathway, providing you a clear pathway and training to reach your potential.
International development and travel opportunities with clients, candidates and offices around the world.
Recognised as one of the Best Companies to Work For with support from Independent Clinical Services, one of the largest healthcare staffing providers in the UK and beyond.

You will need:
You will have experience within Early Education and a passion for business development.
To demonstrate ambition, focus, drive, enthusiasm and professionalism.
Desire to become an expert in your area - we pride ourselves on our specialist knowledge.

Be part of a fast-growing business in an exciting industry
Pulse Child Care Crew is a well-established and leading provider of Early Childhood Professionals to Child Care Centres and Out of School Hours Care throughout Sydney. We support our clients by placing experienced and compliant Early Childhood Teachers, Diploma and Certificate III trained educators as well as Cooks and OSH assistants into permanent and casual roles. Our specialist team of consultants come from various early education backgrounds.

To find out more about this exciting opportunity please call Mandy Sheen on 02 9965 9444 for a confidential chat or email your resume to mandy@childcarecrew.com.au

2. Update the todos key in the ReActConversationState state.

Below is a job advertisement. Perform the following tasks in the order listed below: 
- Extract the raw context of the job advertisement.
- Extract hard and soft skills from the job advertisement.
- Validate skill results by checking for 'both' skill type.
- Extract the requirements mentioned in the advertisement.
- Extract the responsibilities mentioned in the advertisement. 
- Perform G-Eval for 'Correctness' extracted the extracted results. 

[job advertisement]
Readify helps organizations innovate with technology by providing high value software and digital services. Since 2001, Readify has a strong record of helping customers in a range of industries to develop and support innovative software projects. We use agile principles and practices to form autonomous, collaborative and cross-functional teams with our customers. Readify embraces open source software, both as consumers and producers, and offer a generous paid professional development scheme. 
The Role
As a Senior Software Developer you'll provide our clients with an extremely high level of technical expertise and represent Readify as a technical expert in the wider community. You'll have the chance to make an impact in the development of complex, disruptive solutions for a wide range of organizations.
You will be able to apply your passion for technology and problem solving, using the latest, cutting edge technologies whilst working alongside and learning from talented, knowledgeable and experienced software development consultants. 
You will have the opportunity to shape the way that companies deliver software and to work with people who believe in routinely shipping quality software to production. You will need the humility to listen to customers and learn from your peers. 
This is a great role for someone who is self-motivated and loves seeing clients excited about solutions to their business problems. As a consulting organization, there may be the opportunity to travel interstate and collaborate with your interstate colleagues.
The Responsibilities
* Design, develop, test and deliver custom software solutions 
* Directly collaborate with clients on a daily basis
* Form part of an elite delivery team. They will support you and you will be expected to support them. 
Desired Skills and Experience
More than any other skill, we value a willingness to learn and a positive attitude. You'll need to be able to adapt to a wide range of technologies in this role, but we'll support you every step of the way. We expect strong communication skills, deep experience with both front-end and server-side development, and experience with agile software development. We don’t require specific framework or language experience, however we expect candidates to have an interest in skilling up in the .Net stack if they haven’t yet.

We expect you’ll have used 
some
of the following technologies and frameworks to deliver complete solutions:

Javascript / Typescript

React / Angular / Vue

WebPack

HTML5 and CSS3 (Bootstrap, Bulma, etc)

Testing frameworks (Karma, Jasmine, Mocha, Jest etc)

Continuous Integration (CI) / Continuous Delivery (CD) techniques

Strong experience with a server side programming language (C#, Go, Java, Ruby, Python, Rust, Kotlin, F#, Node etc)

Experience with Agile delivery methods

For bonus points, you may also have hands-on experience with the following:

Apache Cordova / React Native / Xamarin

DevOps and Cloud services using AWS / Azure (ARM, CloudFormation)

Experience consulting

Benefits

Work with some of the best, most well-known minds in software development

Less time in meetings, more time shipping

20 days / year of Paid Professional Development

Profit Share Scheme

Mobile, internet and software allowance

$4,200 toolkit allowance renewed every 2 years

Purchased annual leave scheme

·  Casual hours as required (transition to Part-time or Full-time available)
·  Attractive commission based structures
·  Paths for career progression with a trusted national brand
Discover a great place to work at Harvey Norman with over 180 stores nationwide. Harvey Norman is an Australian retail icon with a strong market reputation and performance in the retail categories of furniture and bedding, flooring, bathrooms and kitchen renovations, electrical goods, small appliances, technology and entertainment.

We are seeking an enthusiastic customer service focused Salesperson to join the Coburg Store.

Our Salespeople have an understanding of life at home solutions and a desire to find the best outcome for our customers.

To be successful you must:
·  Have a passion for retail
·  Be highly motivated and results driven person with outstanding customer service and communication skills
·  Enjoy working in a team environment

What we require:
·  Experience in (or ability to work in) a customer focused, successful retail business
·  A high level of Technology and Entertainment product knowledge to support customer queries
·  Ability to service your customers while managing work tasks around their needs
·  Going above and beyond to provide exceptional customer focused problem solving.
·  Experience of resolving customer complaints and making quick decisions to ensure happy customers and timely accurate
services
·  Passion to exceed individual and store sales targets
·  Flexibility across retail trading hours including weekends, public holidays and late night trades

What we offer:
·  Generous staff discounts
·  Attractive commission based structures
·  Fantastic incentive based promotions
·  Harvey Norman is a strong advocate of career progression with a wide support network for professional development
·  An environment where good performance is recognised and rewarded
·  A flexible and positive work environment

If this role exhilarates your passion for a new opportunity then please submit your application for consideration.

3. When you accomplish a TODO, use read_todos to read the TODOs in order to remind yourself of the plan.

Below is a job advertisement. Perform the following tasks in the order listed below: 
- Extract the raw context of the job advertisement.
- Extract hard and soft skills from the job advertisement.
- Validate skill results by checking for 'both' skill type.
- Extract the requirements mentioned in the advertisement.
- Extract the responsibilities mentioned in the advertisement. 
- Perform G-Eval for 'Correctness' extracted the extracted results. 

[job advertisement]
Readify helps organizations innovate with technology by providing high value software and digital services. Since 2001, Readify has a strong record of helping customers in a range of industries to develop and support innovative software projects. We use agile principles and practices to form autonomous, collaborative and cross-functional teams with our customers. Readify embraces open source software, both as consumers and producers, and offer a generous paid professional development scheme. 
The Role
As a Senior Software Developer you'll provide our clients with an extremely high level of technical expertise and represent Readify as a technical expert in the wider community. You'll have the chance to make an impact in the development of complex, disruptive solutions for a wide range of organizations.
You will be able to apply your passion for technology and problem solving, using the latest, cutting edge technologies whilst working alongside and learning from talented, knowledgeable and experienced software development consultants. 
You will have the opportunity to shape the way that companies deliver software and to work with people who believe in routinely shipping quality software to production. You will need the humility to listen to customers and learn from your peers. 
This is a great role for someone who is self-motivated and loves seeing clients excited about solutions to their business problems. As a consulting organization, there may be the opportunity to travel interstate and collaborate with your interstate colleagues.
The Responsibilities
* Design, develop, test and deliver custom software solutions 
* Directly collaborate with clients on a daily basis
* Form part of an elite delivery team. They will support you and you will be expected to support them. 
Desired Skills and Experience
More than any other skill, we value a willingness to learn and a positive attitude. You'll need to be able to adapt to a wide range of technologies in this role, but we'll support you every step of the way. We expect strong communication skills, deep experience with both front-end and server-side development, and experience with agile software development. We don’t require specific framework or language experience, however we expect candidates to have an interest in skilling up in the .Net stack if they haven’t yet.

We expect you’ll have used 
some
of the following technologies and frameworks to deliver complete solutions:

Javascript / Typescript

React / Angular / Vue

WebPack

HTML5 and CSS3 (Bootstrap, Bulma, etc)

Testing frameworks (Karma, Jasmine, Mocha, Jest etc)

Continuous Integration (CI) / Continuous Delivery (CD) techniques

Strong experience with a server side programming language (C#, Go, Java, Ruby, Python, Rust, Kotlin, F#, Node etc)

Experience with Agile delivery methods

For bonus points, you may also have hands-on experience with the following:

Apache Cordova / React Native / Xamarin

DevOps and Cloud services using AWS / Azure (ARM, CloudFormation)

Experience consulting

Benefits

Work with some of the best, most well-known minds in software development

Less time in meetings, more time shipping

20 days / year of Paid Professional Development

Profit Share Scheme

Mobile, internet and software allowance

$4,200 toolkit allowance renewed every 2 years

Purchased annual leave scheme

Below is a job advertisement. Perform the following tasks in the order listed below: 
- Extract the raw context of the job advertisement.
- Extract hard and soft skills from the job advertisement.
- Validate skill results by checking for 'both' skill type.
- Extract the requirements mentioned in the advertisement.
- Extract the responsibilities mentioned in the advertisement. 
- Perform G-Eval for 'Correctness' extracted the extracted results. 

[job advertisement]
​​​Be part of an exciting start-up, innovative outreach service

Deliver high quality mental health services to young people in the local community

Full time fixed term contract (June 2020) based in Karratha

We are connected, proud of our impact, creative, high performing, inclusive and welcoming… are you?

headspace
, Australia's National Youth Mental Health Foundation, provides vital early intervention mental health services to 12-25 year olds. Anglicare WA is working in partnership with a number of stakeholders to extend the provision of 
headspace
services and supports to young people and families in the Pilbara region of Western Australia through a new, innovative outreach model
.

About us

Working closely with a range of local health and community partner organisations, the fairly new outreach focused 
headspace Pilbara 
service provides a holistic, wrap around primary health care service for young people in the Pilbara with mild to moderate mental health problems affecting their wellbeing.   Services span the core areas of mental health, physical health, vocational support and alcohol and drug services.  The 
headspace Pilbara
service, in particular, works with a number of local Aboriginal youth and families and has a focus on community capacity building.

About the role

We are now looking for a highly skilled, enthusiastic and motivated person to fill the pivotal role of Youth Wellbeing Worker 
headspace Pilbara
on a full time fixed term contract basis until June 2020.  This role, based in Karratha, will provide comprehensive intake, initial screening assessment and brief interventions for young people and their families along with facilitating or involving activities or outings as part of the response. In addition, you will design and coordinate events increasing the profile of 
headspace Pilbara
, delivering messages around mental health literacy and stigmas along with building effective relationships with the community and other service providers.

About you

To be successful in this role you will have:

Substantial experience in and knowledge of youth mental health support and intervention

Tertiary level qualifications in youth work, social work, counselling or related discipline

Previous experience and proven ability in youth program facilitation and coordination

Well-developed stakeholder engagement skills.

Highly developed cultural competency which will enable you to easily engage and build trust with people from diverse backgrounds, in particular Aboriginal communities.

Experience and/or knowledge of work in regional and remote context

About our values

While your qualifications and experience tell us part of your story, your values and attitude speak louder still.  You will have a strong alignment with our organisational values of courage, respect, inclusion, compassion, empowerment and trust. To operate successfully in this exciting and dynamic, but relatively new environment, you will need bounds of tenacity and resilience, be a strong and effective communicator and facilitator, and thrive on forming long lasting relationships.

In return, you will be rewarded with a career building clinical role, supported by an extended team of people who are proud and passionate about walking with people on their journey to thriving.  Other benefits include attractive remuneration with generous remote allowances and access to salary packaging.

The successful candidate must possess a current National Police Clearance valid within one year, Working With Children Check and a WA Drivers Licence.

For more information, please contact Samara Clark, Manager, 
headspace 
Pilbara on 0436 655 379.

How to Apply

To be considered, 
applications 
must include a current detailed resume and covering letter.  To apply, please click on the 
apply button
and follow the prompts.

Applications close 12 May 2019.

Anglicare WA is deeply committed to reconciliation, inclusion as well as equal employment opportunity and encourages applications from diverse backgrounds, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, people from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds and people with disabilities.

Unsolicited referrals from recruitment agencies will not be accepted.

```
Be part of an exciting start-up, innovative outreach service

Deliver high quality mental health services to young people in the local community

Full time fixed term contract (June 2020) based in Karratha

We are connected, proud of our impact, creative, high performing, inclusive and welcoming… are you?

headspace, Australia's National Youth Mental Health Foundation, provides vital early intervention mental health services to 12-25 year olds. Anglicare WA is working in partnership with a number of stakeholders to extend the provision of headspace services and supports to young people and families in the Pilbara region of Western Australia through a new, innovative outreach model.

About us

Working closely with a range of local health and community partner organisations, the fairly new outreach focused headspace Pilbara service provides a holistic, wrap around primary health care service for young people in the Pilbara with mild to moderate mental health problems affecting their wellbeing.   Services span the core areas of mental health, physical health, vocational support and alcohol and drug services.  The headspace Pilbara service, in particular, works with a number of local Aboriginal youth and families and has a focus on community capacity building.

About the role

We are now looking for a highly skilled, enthusiastic and motivated person to fill the pivotal role of Youth Wellbeing Worker headspace Pilbara on a full time fixed term contract basis until June 2020.  This role, based in Karratha, will provide comprehensive intake, initial screening assessment and brief interventions for young people and their families along with facilitating or involving activities or outings as part of the response. In addition, you will design and coordinate events increasing the profile of headspace Pilbara, delivering messages around mental health literacy and stigmas along with building effective relationships with the community and other service providers.

About you

To be successful in this role you will have:

Substantial experience in and knowledge of youth mental health support and intervention

Tertiary level qualifications in youth work, social work, counselling or related discipline

Previous experience and proven ability in youth program facilitation and coordination

Well-developed stakeholder engagement skills.

Highly developed cultural competency which will enable you to easily engage and build trust with people from diverse backgrounds, in particular Aboriginal communities.

Experience and/or knowledge of work in regional and remote context

About our values

While your qualifications and experience tell us part of your story, your values and attitude speak louder still.  You will have a strong alignment with our organisational values of courage, respect, inclusion, compassion, empowerment and trust. To operate successfully in this exciting and dynamic, but relatively new environment, you will need bounds of tenacity and resilience, be a strong and effective communicator and facilitator, and thrive on forming long lasting relationships.

In return, you will be rewarded with a career building clinical role, supported by an extended team of people who are proud and passionate about walking with people on their journey to thriving.  Other benefits include attractive remuneration with generous remote allowances and access to salary packaging.

The successful candidate must possess a current National Police Clearance valid within one year, Working With Children Check and a WA Drivers Licence.

For more information, please contact Samara Clark, Manager, headspace Pilbara on 0436 655 379.

How to Apply

To be considered, applications must include a current detailed resume and covering letter.  To apply, please click on the apply button and follow the prompts.

Applications close 12 May 2019.

Anglicare WA is deeply committed to reconciliation, inclusion as well as equal employment opportunity and encourages applications from diverse backgrounds, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, people from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds and people with disabilities.

Unsolicited referrals from recruitment agencies will not be accepted.

job_ads:
[{'ad_text': "Be part of an exciting start-up, innovative outreach service

Deliver high quality mental health services to young people in the local community

Full time fixed term contract (June 2020) based in Karratha

We are connected, proud of our impact, creative, high performing, inclusive and welcoming… are you?

headspace
, Australia's National Youth Mental Health Foundation, provides vital early intervention mental health services to 12-25 year olds. Anglicare WA is working in partnership with a number of stakeholders to extend the provision of 
headspace
services and supports to young people and families in the Pilbara region of Western Australia through a new, innovative outreach model
.

About us

Working closely with a range of local health and community partner organisations, the fairly new outreach focused 
headspace Pilbara 
service provides a holistic, wrap around primary health care service for young people in the Pilbara with mild to moderate mental health problems affecting their wellbeing.   Services span the core areas of mental health, physical health, vocational support and alcohol and drug services.  The 
headspace Pilbara
service, in particular, works with a number of local Aboriginal youth and families and has a focus on community capacity building.

About the role

We are now looking for a highly skilled, enthusiastic and motivated person to fill the pivotal role of Youth Wellbeing Worker 
headspace Pilbara
on a full time fixed term contract basis until June 2020.  This role, based in Karratha, will provide comprehensive intake, initial screening assessment and brief interventions for young people and their families along with facilitating or involving activities or outings as part of the response. In addition, you will design and coordinate events increasing the profile of 
headspace Pilbara
, delivering messages around mental health literacy and stigmas along with building effective relationships with the community and other service providers.

About you

To be successful in this role you will have:

Substantial experience in and knowledge of youth mental health support and intervention

Tertiary level qualifications in youth work, social work, counselling or related discipline

Previous experience and proven ability in youth program facilitation and coordination

Well-developed stakeholder engagement skills.

Highly developed cultural competency which will enable you to easily engage and build trust with people from diverse backgrounds, in particular Aboriginal communities.

Experience and/or knowledge of work in regional and remote context

About our values

While your qualifications and experience tell us part of your story, your values and attitude speak louder still.  You will have a strong alignment with our organisational values of courage, respect, inclusion, compassion, empowerment and trust. To operate successfully in this exciting and dynamic, but relatively new environment, you will need bounds of tenacity and resilience, be a strong and effective communicator and facilitator, and thrive on forming long lasting relationships.

In return, you will be rewarded with a career building clinical role, supported by an extended team of people who are proud and passionate about walking with people on their journey to thriving.  Other benefits include attractive remuneration with generous remote allowances and access to salary packaging.

The successful candidate must possess a current National Police Clearance valid within one year, Working With Children Check and a WA Drivers Licence.

For more information, please contact Samara Clark, Manager, 
headspace 
Pilbara on 0436 655 379.

How to Apply

To be considered, 
applications 
must include a current detailed resume and covering letter.  To apply, please click on the 
apply button
and follow the prompts.

Applications close 12 May 2019.

Anglicare WA is deeply committed to reconciliation, inclusion as well as equal employment opportunity and encourages applications from diverse backgrounds, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, people from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds and people with disabilities.

Unsolicited referrals from recruitment agencies will not be accepted."}]

Below is a job advertisement. Perform the following tasks in the order listed below: 
- Extract the raw context of the job advertisement.
- Extract hard and soft skills from the job advertisement.
- Validate skill results by checking for 'both' skill type.
- Extract the requirements mentioned in the advertisement.
- Extract the responsibilities mentioned in the advertisement. 
- Perform G-Eval for 'Correctness' extracted the extracted results. 

[job advertisement]
​​​Be part of an exciting start-up, innovative outreach service

Deliver high quality mental health services to young people in the local community

Full time fixed term contract (June 2020) based in Karratha

We are connected, proud of our impact, creative, high performing, inclusive and welcoming… are you?

headspace
, Australia's National Youth Mental Health Foundation, provides vital early intervention mental health services to 12-25 year olds. Anglicare WA is working in partnership with a number of stakeholders to extend the provision of 
headspace
services and supports to young people and families in the Pilbara region of Western Australia through a new, innovative outreach model
.

About us

Working closely with a range of local health and community partner organisations, the fairly new outreach focused 
headspace Pilbara 
service provides a holistic, wrap around primary health care service for young people in the Pilbara with mild to moderate mental health problems affecting their wellbeing.   Services span the core areas of mental health, physical health, vocational support and alcohol and drug services.  The 
headspace Pilbara
service, in particular, works with a number of local Aboriginal youth and families and has a focus on community capacity building.

About the role

We are now looking for a highly skilled, enthusiastic and motivated person to fill the pivotal role of Youth Wellbeing Worker 
headspace Pilbara
on a full time fixed term contract basis until June 2020.  This role, based in Karratha, will provide comprehensive intake, initial screening assessment and brief interventions for young people and their families along with facilitating or involving activities or outings as part of the response. In addition, you will design and coordinate events increasing the profile of 
headspace Pilbara
, delivering messages around mental health literacy and stigmas along with building effective relationships with the community and other service providers.

About you

To be successful in this role you will have:

Substantial experience in and knowledge of youth mental health support and intervention

Tertiary level qualifications in youth work, social work, counselling or related discipline

Previous experience and proven ability in youth program facilitation and coordination

Well-developed stakeholder engagement skills.

Highly developed cultural competency which will enable you to easily engage and build trust with people from diverse backgrounds, in particular Aboriginal communities.

Experience and/or knowledge of work in regional and remote context

About our values

While your qualifications and experience tell us part of your story, your values and attitude speak louder still.  You will have a strong alignment with our organisational values of courage, respect, inclusion, compassion, empowerment and trust. To operate successfully in this exciting and dynamic, but relatively new environment, you will need bounds of tenacity and resilience, be a strong and effective communicator and facilitator, and thrive on forming long lasting relationships.

In return, you will be rewarded with a career building clinical role, supported by an extended team of people who are proud and passionate about walking with people on their journey to thriving.  Other benefits include attractive remuneration with generous remote allowances and access to salary packaging.

The successful candidate must possess a current National Police Clearance valid within one year, Working With Children Check and a WA Drivers Licence.

For more information, please contact Samara Clark, Manager, 
headspace 
Pilbara on 0436 655 379.

How to Apply

To be considered, 
applications 
must include a current detailed resume and covering letter.  To apply, please click on the 
apply button
and follow the prompts.

Applications close 12 May 2019.

Anglicare WA is deeply committed to reconciliation, inclusion as well as equal employment opportunity and encourages applications from diverse backgrounds, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, people from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds and people with disabilities.

Unsolicited referrals from recruitment agencies will not be accepted.

```
Be part of an exciting start-up, innovative outreach service

Deliver high quality mental health services to young people in the local community

Full time fixed term contract (June 2020) based in Karratha

We are connected, proud of our impact, creative, high performing, inclusive and welcoming… are you?

headspace, Australia's National Youth Mental Health Foundation, provides vital early intervention mental health services to 12-25 year olds. Anglicare WA is working in partnership with a number of stakeholders to extend the provision of headspace services and supports to young people and families in the Pilbara region of Western Australia through a new, innovative outreach model.

About us

Working closely with a range of local health and community partner organisations, the fairly new outreach focused headspace Pilbara service provides a holistic, wrap around primary health care service for young people in the Pilbara with mild to moderate mental health problems affecting their wellbeing.   Services span the core areas of mental health, physical health, vocational support and alcohol and drug services.  The headspace Pilbara service, in particular, works with a number of local Aboriginal youth and families and has a focus on community capacity building.

About the role

We are now looking for a highly skilled, enthusiastic and motivated person to fill the pivotal role of Youth Wellbeing Worker headspace Pilbara on a full time fixed term contract basis until June 2020.  This role, based in Karratha, will provide comprehensive intake, initial screening assessment and brief interventions for young people and their families along with facilitating or involving activities or outings as part of the response. In addition, you will design and coordinate events increasing the profile of headspace Pilbara, delivering messages around mental health literacy and stigmas along with building effective relationships with the community and other service providers.

About you

To be successful in this role you will have:

Substantial experience in and knowledge of youth mental health support and intervention

Tertiary level qualifications in youth work, social work, counselling or related discipline

Previous experience and proven ability in youth program facilitation and coordination

Well-developed stakeholder engagement skills.

Highly developed cultural competency which will enable you to easily engage and build trust with people from diverse backgrounds, in particular Aboriginal communities.

Experience and/or knowledge of work in regional and remote context

About our values

While your qualifications and experience tell us part of your story, your values and attitude speak louder still.  You will have a strong alignment with our organisational values of courage, respect, inclusion, compassion, empowerment and trust. To operate successfully in this exciting and dynamic, but relatively new environment, you will need bounds of tenacity and resilience, be a strong and effective communicator and facilitator, and thrive on forming long lasting relationships.

In return, you will be rewarded with a career building clinical role, supported by an extended team of people who are proud and passionate about walking with people on their journey to thriving.  Other benefits include attractive remuneration with generous remote allowances and access to salary packaging.

The successful candidate must possess a current National Police Clearance valid within one year, Working With Children Check and a WA Drivers Licence.

For more information, please contact Samara Clark, Manager, headspace Pilbara on 0436 655 379.

How to Apply

To be considered, applications must include a current detailed resume and covering letter.  To apply, please click on the apply button and follow the prompts.

Applications close 12 May 2019.

Anglicare WA is deeply committed to reconciliation, inclusion as well as equal employment opportunity and encourages applications from diverse backgrounds, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, people from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds and people with disabilities.

Unsolicited referrals from recruitment agencies will not be accepted.

Below is a job advertisement. Perform the following tasks in the order listed below: 
- Extract the raw context of the job advertisement.
- Extract hard and soft skills from the job advertisement.

[job advertisement]
WesTrac has set the benchmark in equipment solutions, providing customers across Western Australia, New South Wales and Australian Capital Territory with award winning support across the mining, construction and transport industries. WesTrac’s vision is to be the Customers First Choice in Equipment Management Solutions. To achieve this, we put safety first and have the right people in the right roles

About the role

Reporting to the Area Manager of the North West, the Parts Supervisor in Port Hedland is responsible for leading the branch warehouse to implement strategy and continuous improvement initiatuives whilst also ensuring positive engagement of team members and customers.

In this role, you will be responsible for;

Providing leadership to a team to ensure KPIs are met, reviewed and reported on

Identify cost reduction opportunities and improvements within the supply chain

Ensure consistent data reporting and evaluation

Identify issues, situations and opportunities and provide effective solutions

Manage the successful contractual obligations with external service providers to ensure fulfilment of service requirements

This role is a Port Hedland residential role, working Monday – Friday. Relocation assistance will be provided for the successful candidate

About you

The role will require you to have;

At least ten years experience of logistics and warehousing

Experience with CAT systems such as DBS, SIS, TMI essential

Experience leading a workforce

Sound knowledge of warehouse management systems

Excellent knowledge of WHS (Workplace Health and Safety) Legislation coupled with demonstrated application within a warehouse environment

Company Benefits:

WesTrac offers competitive remuneration packages and many other benefits which include:

Salary sacrificing options i.e. airline membership, motor vehicle etc.

Flexible work arrangements

Income Protection Insurance

Paid Parental Leave

Discounted CAT products

Wellness Program

Partner Discount network

Employee Assistance Program (EAP)

Further education assistance

Discounted gym membership

Discounted health insurance

At WesTrac our primary focus is our people. We know that our success is the result of more than 3,000 talented people working together to achieve amazing outcomes. Now, as we look to the future and our goal of becoming the first choice in equipment solutions, we're more focused than ever on harnessing the best talent for our business.

NB: WesTrac recognise the value of and strongly support the principles of equal employment opportunities in the workplace. We reserve the right to withdraw this ad prior to the closing date.

[job advertisement]
Summary
ITtelligent is an IT business which focuses on proactive IT support 24/7 designed for organisations from as little as 5 computers up to 250 computers and, unlike many of its competitors, guarantees a 5-minute response.
ITtelligent not only offers a flat fee but also does not force its clients to lock in to a costly contract. Their clients are able to opt out at any point in time and in knowing this ITtelligent works above and beyond to keep its clients happy.
ITtelligent has grown enormously since its humble beginnings in 2006 where owner and director Robert Adelman launched ITtelligent from his own lounge room
Position Summary:
Based at 2 of our clients offices in Sydney (CBD and Surrey Hills) the Level 2 Support Engineer is responsible for the upkeep of ITtelligent clients systems.
The occupier of this role is responsible for:

2nd Level HelpDesk

Excellent knowledge of desktops (preferably HP)

Support and maintain backup, virus protection, internet and remote access solutions

Manage and support MS Server environments including AD

Strong troubleshooting skills across user and application support

Office 365 Administration and management

Qualifications and Experience

Minimum two years of experience in the operation and support of Windows Desktop operating systems

Windows Server Experience

Active Directory experience

Linux experience is highly desirable

ShadowProtect and/or Veeam is highly desired

Excellent phone manner

Excellent Customer service skills

Similar experience in a Helpdesk role

ITIL Experience is desirable

Microsoft and/or Vendor Qualification are highly favourable

Good command of the English language

Ability to multi-task and prioritise work based on client impact and effort required for resolution

What we can offer you...

Career Progression Opportunities

Excellent learning opportunities with exposure to variety of technologies

A supportive and team orientated environment

Opportunity to work on cutting edge technology projects and leading vendors

Working Environment
Employee safety and well-being is paramount to the company
ITtelligent is a team based organisation. Within the company, innovative thinking and team wide participation is encouraged and nurtured

ITtelligent has access to many client clients confidential systems, therefore client confidentiality is required by each of its staff.

As the successful applicant, this role will see your responsibilities include:

Actioning opportunities via all channels including in person, phone, email, etc

Developing strategies generating project opportunities

Achieving agreed project sales targets

Managing B2B relationships and key stakeholders with project sale partners

Ensuring sale quality to minimise cancellation rates

Updating and maintaining the CRM system

Weekly sales reporting

Completing market research and competitor project profiling

Delivering presentations to large stakeholder and customer groups

Dealing with customers who purchase our product

As the ideal applicant you will possess:

Current Real Estate Licence and equivalent experience

Demonstrated experience in off the plan project sales

Outstanding interpersonal and communication skills

Highly developed abilities in stakeholder/relationship management

About working for Frasers Property Australia:

At Frasers Property Australia, we are driven by a belief that ‘
experience matters’,
. Understanding the human side of property is our greatest asset and inspires our workplaces. We maintain an environment of equality where all staff members are supported in their efforts to achieve their full potential. We implement policies and work practices that encourage flexible work options to assist all staff to balance their work, life and family responsibilities, including our paid parental leave scheme and flexible work options."}]

4. Reflect on what you've done and the TODO.

6. Continue this process until you have completed all the TODO items created.", additional_kwargs={}, response_metadata={}, id='26aaf49e-3b74-42d6-b04e-048e67b8267b'), HumanMessage(content="
Below is a job advertisement. Perform the following tasks in the order listed below: 
- Extract the raw context of the job advertisement.
- Extract hard and soft skills from the job advertisement.
- Validate skill results by checking for 'both' skill type.
- Extract the requirements mentioned in the advertisement.
- Extract the responsibilities mentioned in the advertisement. 
- Perform G-Eval for 'Correctness' extracted the extracted results. 

[job advertisement]
Crewe Sharp Medical is one of Australia's leading nursing agencies, Providing health Care workers to community and aged care providers throughout Australia for over thirteen years.

Crewe Sharp Medical is excited to announce a recruitment partnership with Benetas for their new facility in Heidelberg.

Who is Benetas?

Benetas is a not for profit organisation dedicated to supporting older Victorians, their friends and carers, through a range of aged care and in-home services.  Benetas is committed to our reputation as a truly great place to work.  We care about our people’s health and wellbeing and invest significantly in their development.  We take pride in being a diverse and inclusive employer.  We respect and value differences and encourage people of all ages and backgrounds to apply.  Benetas is a recognised leader in Gender Equality, having been awarded an Employer of Choice citation for 12 years in a row.

Exciting times at ‘The Views’

Benetas is undergoing a period of significant growth and change in the local Heidelberg area, with our purpose-built, 103 bed aged care site opening in late October 2018.  Based on contemporary person-centred care using the latest technology and equipment, The Views at Heidelberg will provide apartment style living for residents.

We’re not talking good care, we’re talking great care!

By forming genuine relationships with residents and their loved ones, you will coordinate and support residents to make choices and decisions about how they spend their day-to-day life within their apartment.  You will use your interpersonal skills and knowledge of each resident in their apartment to create a truly homelike experience.  As a Personal Carer you will form part of the Apartment care team, and be supported by an expert team of clinicians to ensure the resident’s individual clinical needs are managed appropriately.

For our residents, each day is about choice and flexibility, not the daily routine.

What training and skills do I need?

Certificate III in Individual Care (or equivalent)

Be able to assist with medication

Comfortable working semi-autonomously

Upbeat, friendly and client-focused

Valid working rights

Police check

Why work for Benetas?

Nearly 80% of staff say that Benetas is a truly great place to work.  At Benetas you will be provided with:

A safe and supportive work environment where people are valued and encouraged to share their ideas

A strong learning culture where you are in the driver’s seat of your ongoing professional development

Rewarding work that supports our clients to have a positive experience of ageing

Working in a trusted and values based organisation focused on quality and growth

Competitive Salary (with salary packaging and meal & entertainment benefits)

Successful candidates will complete a comprehensive training program including buddy shifts, so you can confidently hit the ground running.
More information and importantly, how to apply…

To register your interest to be part of this exciting time, please send your cover letter and resume by clicking the Apply button.

For more information, please contact our friendly recruitment team on 9510 5299

```
Crewe Sharp Medical is one of Australia's leading nursing agencies, Providing health Care workers to community and aged care providers throughout Australia for over thirteen years.

Crewe Sharp Medical is excited to announce a recruitment partnership with Benetas for their new facility in Heidelberg.

Who is Benetas?

Benetas is a not for profit organisation dedicated to supporting older Victorians, their friends and carers, through a range of aged care and in-home services.  Benetas is committed to our reputation as a truly great place to work.  We care about our people’s health and wellbeing and invest significantly in their development.  We take pride in being a diverse and inclusive employer.  We respect and value differences and encourage people of all ages and backgrounds to apply.  Benetas is a recognised leader in Gender Equality, having been awarded an Employer of Choice citation for 12 years in a row.

Exciting times at ‘The Views’

Benetas is undergoing a period of significant growth and change in the local Heidelberg area, with our purpose-built, 103 bed aged care site opening in late October 2018.  Based on contemporary person-centred care using the latest technology and equipment, The Views at Heidelberg will provide apartment style living for residents.

We’re not talking good care, we’re talking great care!

By forming genuine relationships with residents and their loved ones, you will coordinate and support residents to make choices and decisions about how they spend their day-to-day life within their apartment.  You will use your interpersonal skills and knowledge of each resident in their apartment to create a truly homelike experience.  As a Personal Carer you will form part of the Apartment care team, and be supported by an expert team of clinicians to ensure the resident’s individual clinical needs are managed appropriately.

For our residents, each day is about choice and flexibility, not the daily routine.

What training and skills do I need?

Certificate III in Individual Care (or equivalent)

Be able to assist with medication

Comfortable working semi-autonomously

Upbeat, friendly and client-focused

Valid working rights

Police check

Why work for Benetas?

Nearly 80% of staff say that Benetas is a truly great place to work.  At Benetas you will be provided with:

A safe and supportive work environment where people are valued and encouraged to share their ideas

A strong learning culture where you are in the driver’s seat of your ongoing professional development

Rewarding work that supports our clients to have a positive experience of ageing

Working in a trusted and values based organisation focused on quality and growth

Competitive Salary (with salary packaging and meal & entertainment benefits)

Successful candidates will complete a comprehensive training program including buddy shifts, so you can confidently hit the ground running.
More information and importantly, how to apply…

To register your interest to be part of this exciting time, please send your cover letter and resume by clicking the Apply button.

For more information, please contact our friendly recruitment team on 9510 5299

[job advertisement]
This exciting opportunity is for someone who displays a passion for guest services, and who has proven experience in a customer service supervisor role.

Reporting to the Hotel Manager, you will be part of a Front Office Team and have the ability to ensure that the core of hotel operations and guest services supports the high standards and reputation of the hotel.

We are a fast-growing hotel group based in Canberra, affiliated with companies involved in construction and property development. The company’s first hotel, Abode Gungahlin opened in 2010 and was the first of its kind for the region. Now with seven hotels across Canberra and surrounds, the company continues to cement its position as a leader in the hotel and hospitality sector.

As a growing Canberra brand, we are always looking for new team members who have experience in the hospitality and tourism industry and possess stand-out customer service skills.

Job tasks & responsibilities

Minimum 12 months experience in a customer service supervisor role

Responsible for the functions of the Front Office

Experience in resolving complaints

Strong communications and interpersonal skills

Excellent attention to detail

Be an enthusiastic team player

Work well under pressure

Have a strong customer focus.

A knowledge of Opera PMS is desirable

Able to work a rotating roster including weekends

Raw Job Advertisement Text**  
```
About the company
: 
My client has been an industry leader for the past 25 years in the Insurance and Construction Industry. Due to rapid growth we are seeking a Site Supervisor to join the friendly team. They provide a social culture, supportive environment and job security with the volume of work that has been secured.

About the Role
: The Site Supervisor will be trade qualified and have previous experience in a similar role. Reporting to the General Manager, the objective of the role is to supervise work sites ensure all obligations are adhered to.

Duties:

Engage, coordinate and manage trades

Keep full site documentation of all day to day activities on-site

Manage on-site personnel and coordinate site activity

Review progress against plans

Update project schedules

Liaising with clients and trade contractors

Ensure all work conforms to legislative and OH&S criteria

Conducting inspections pf projects

Adhering to KPI's

Skills and Experience:

Experience working in Construction/Insurance

Trade or Tertiary Qualified in a Building related discipline

Excellent communication skills

Excellent organisation and time management skills

Strong attention to detail

Valid motor vehicle licence

Benefits:

Long term opportunity

Career development on offer

Competitive salary and ongoing rewards

Please apply for the role should you satisfy the requirements by sending your resume in WORD Format.
```

---

**2. Hard Skills (12)**  
- Construction  
- Insurance  
- Trade qualification  
- Building‑related discipline  
- Motor vehicle licence  
- Project scheduling  
- Legislative compliance  
- OH&S compliance  
- Site inspections  
- KPI adherence  
- Documentation management  
- Personnel coordination  

**3. Soft Skills (5)**  
- Excellent communication  
- Excellent organisation  
- Time‑management  
- Attention to detail  
- Coordination  

**4. Requirements (8)**  
1. Trade qualified  
2. Previous experience in a similar role  
3. Ability to supervise work sites  
4. Ensure all obligations are adhered to  
5. Report to the General Manager  
6. Engage, coordinate and manage trades  
7. Keep full site documentation of day‑to‑day activities  
8. Manage on‑site personnel and coordinate site activity  

**5. Responsibilities (9)**  
1. Engage, coordinate and manage trades  
2. Keep full site documentation of all day‑to‑day activities on‑site  
3. Manage on‑site personnel and coordinate site activity  
4. Review progress against plans  
5. Update project schedules  
6. Liaise with clients and trade contractors  
7. Ensure all work conforms to legislative and OH&S criteria  
8. Conduct inspections of projects  
9. Adhere to KPI’s  

**6. G‑Eval for Correctness**

Below is a job advertisement. Perform the following tasks in the order listed below: 
- Extract the raw context of the job advertisement.
- Extract hard and soft skills from the job advertisement.

[job advertisement]
Kia Ora, New Zealand needs you!

We are excited to partner with 
HazardCo
to recruit a key role in their team. HazardCo are a fast-growing and evolving company providing Health and Safety systems to tradies and other enterprises across New Zealand.

Being at the forefront of changing safety culture, HazardCo has built a user-friendly cloud-based web application to help their customers implement great health and safety practices in their workplace.

The Job at Hand:
Hazard Co are looking for a JavaScript Engineer / Full-Stack Developer to spearhead the development of Hybrid Mobile Applications and a Web Platform. In this role you will be a key part of the future design/ architecture and build of the features and overall product.

Key Responsibilities:

Develop user-friendly applications across both iOS and Android in the cloud

Assist product architects to design and prototype software, applications and functionality

Support, develop and train others within your team

Contribute to the CI/CD drive across your team and within HazardCo

Perform thorough testing and data validation

To be successful in this role
you need to be a team player, with the drive to develop intuitive applications that are heavily end-user focused. You would have come from a diverse mobile development background, likely having worked on various projects within different markets / industries throughout your career. You have worked with AWS-based microservice architecture before and are an advocate for CI/CD. Never happy with what is current, you are always looking at what could/ will be next – you are innovative and agile always wanting to improve yourself and your products.

TechStack:

Both Client and Server-side development with JavaScript frameworks

Pref - Angular / NativeScript and Node.js

AWS / Azure for build, deployment and CI

Exposure to non-relational Databases

Pref – DynamoDB

Must have some experience integrating hybrid mobile applications

If you feel that you could really make an impact with the HazardCo team and would be keen to find out more about this role (or apply), you can apply here or give Kane Landers a call on (04) 499 9471. Alternatively, you can email your CV and Cover Letter to Kane.Landers@h2r.co.nz with ‘JavasScript Developer’ in the subject line.

```
Kia Ora, New Zealand needs you!

We are excited to partner with 
HazardCo
to recruit a key role in their team. HazardCo are a fast-growing and evolving company providing Health and Safety systems to tradies and other enterprises across New Zealand.

Being at the forefront of changing safety culture, HazardCo has built a user-friendly cloud-based web application to help their customers implement great health and safety practices in their workplace.

The Job at Hand:
Hazard Co are looking for a JavaScript Engineer / Full-Stack Developer to spearhead the development of Hybrid Mobile Applications and a Web Platform. In this role you will be a key part of the future design/ architecture and build of the features and overall product.

Key Responsibilities:

Develop user-friendly applications across both iOS and Android in the cloud

Assist product architects to design and prototype software, applications and functionality

Support, develop and train others within your team

Contribute to the CI/CD drive across your team and within HazardCo

Perform thorough testing and data validation

To be successful in this role
you need to be a team player, with the drive to develop intuitive applications that are heavily end-user focused. You would have come from a diverse mobile development background, likely having worked on various projects within different markets / industries throughout your career. You have worked with AWS-based microservice architecture before and are an advocate for CI/CD. Never happy with what is current, you are always looking at what could/ will be next – you are innovative and agile always wanting to improve yourself and your products.

TechStack:

Both Client and Server-side development with JavaScript frameworks

Pref - Angular / NativeScript and Node.js

AWS / Azure for build, deployment and CI

Exposure to non-relational Databases

Pref – DynamoDB

Must have some experience integrating hybrid mobile applications

If you feel that you could really make an impact with the HazardCo team and would be keen to find out more about this role (or apply), you can apply here or give Kane Landers a call on (04) 499 9471. Alternatively, you can email your CV and Cover Letter to Kane.Landers@h2r.co.nz with ‘JavasScript Developer’ in the subject line.
```

1. JavaScript  
2. Angular  
3. NativeScript  
4. Node.js  
5. AWS  
6. Azure  
7. CI/CD  
8. Non‑relational Databases  
9. DynamoDB  
10. Hybrid Mobile Applications  

### Soft Skills (6)
1. Team player  
2. End‑user focused  
3. Innovative  
4. Agile  
5. Self‑improvement oriented  
6. Advocate for CI/CD  

### Validation

---

1. Experience with AWS‑based microservice architecture

4. Experience with JavaScript frameworks (client and server side)  
5. Experience with Angular or NativeScript  
6. Experience with Node.js  
7. Experience with AWS or Azure for build, deployment, and CI  
8. Experience with non‑relational databases (preferably DynamoDB)  
9. Ability to develop user‑friendly applications across iOS and Android in the cloud  
10. Ability to support, develop, and train others within the team

---

### Responsibilities

- Extract the raw context of the job advertisement.
- Extract hard and soft skills from the job advertisement.

[job advertisement]
Casual & Part-Time Opportunities

Do you want a rewarding job that makes a difference to the lives of older people?

If YES, 
Apply now!

This is a great opportunity for experienced and passionate professionals to join our team at Benhome, located in Maitland NSW.

As part of our commitment to providing quality aged care we are seeking qualified carers to join our collaborative clinical care team at RFBI Benhome Masonic Village (in Maitland, NSW) on a Casual and part-time basis. We are seeking motivated and experienced individuals, with a commitment to providing quality care to aged residents. As we operate a 24/7 facility the successful applicants will need to be ready and available to care for our residents.

At RFBI we aim to meet the individual preferences of our residents whilst providing the highest possible care. Within this multifaceted role, your key focus will be to undertake a wide range of personal and clinical care services to assist our residents with their daily living needs.

You will need:

An enthusiastic and motivated approach

A Certificate III in Aged Care plus relevant industry experience

A Current First Aid Certificate

A Current Police Check Certificate

An understanding of WHS responsibilities including manual handling principles

Your responsibilities will include:

Providing a wide range of personal care services and basic clinical care to residents

Delivering care management for diabetes, arthritis and other conditions

Assist residents and follow directions of Supervisor/Manager to achieve best possible person centred care and achieve our resident wishes

About you:

A passionate individual who is dedicated about delivering the best possible care to our residents

Effective communication skills and the ability to develop understanding relationships with residents

Availability for a wide variety of shifts; morning, evening and night

About RFBI:

Royal Freemasons' Benevolent Institution (RFBI) was established in 1880 to help people in need.

RFBI has become a leading aged care provider with a vision to provide quality aged care services that are accessible by all people and has a positive impact on their lives.

RFBI operates 21 residential aged care villages and 20 retirement villages across NSW and ACT.

RFBI offers a range of home and community services across NSW and ACT to support older Australians to remain living in their own home.

Note:

You must have or be able to obtain a current National Police Check (AFP Code 22) and be willing to undergo a Pre-Employment Functional Assessment to be eligible for the role.

All applicants must be eligible to work in Australia.

To be successful you will demonstrate your passion to make a difference in the lives of our residents and to work with them to ensure they receive the highest possible care, tailored to their needs and preferences.

Applications Close:
Sunday 2nd June 2019

Please apply with your current Resume and a cover letter with a summary of why this is the role for you.

If you feel this is the right role for you, don't wait, apply now!

Join a supportive and inclusive team environment

An opportunity to work within a growing organisation

Increase your take home pay with salary packaging opportunities

Ongoing learning and development opportunities

Raw Job Advertisement Text**  
```
Casual & Part-Time Opportunities

Do you want a rewarding job that makes a difference to the lives of older people?

If YES, 
Apply now!

This is a great opportunity for experienced and passionate professionals to join our team at Benhome, located in Maitland NSW.

As part of our commitment to providing quality aged care we are seeking qualified carers to join our collaborative clinical care team at RFBI Benhome Masonic Village (in Maitland, NSW) on a Casual and part-time basis. We are seeking motivated and experienced individuals, with a commitment to providing quality care to aged residents. As we operate a 24/7 facility the successful applicants will need to be ready and available to care for our residents.

At RFBI we aim to meet the individual preferences of our residents whilst providing the highest possible care. Within this multifaceted role, your key focus will be to undertake a wide range of personal and clinical care services to assist our residents with their daily living needs.

You will need:

An enthusiastic and motivated approach

A Certificate III in Aged Care plus relevant industry experience

A Current First Aid Certificate

A Current Police Check Certificate

An understanding of WHS responsibilities including manual handling principles

Your responsibilities will include:

Providing a wide range of personal care services and basic clinical care to residents

Delivering care management for diabetes, arthritis and other conditions

Assist residents and follow directions of Supervisor/Manager to achieve best possible person centred care and achieve our resident wishes

About you:

A passionate individual who is dedicated about delivering the best possible care to our residents

Effective communication skills and the ability to develop understanding relationships with residents

Availability for a wide variety of shifts; morning, evening and night

About RFBI:

Royal Freemasons' Benevolent Institution (RFBI) was established in 1880 to help people in need.

RFBI has become a leading aged care provider with a vision to provide quality aged care services that are accessible by all people and has a positive impact on their lives.

RFBI operates 21 residential aged care villages and 20 retirement villages across NSW and ACT.

RFBI offers a range of home and community services across NSW and ACT to support older Australians to remain living in their own home.

Note:

You must have or be able to obtain a current National Police Check (AFP Code 22) and be willing to undergo a Pre-Employment Functional Assessment to be eligible for the role.

All applicants must be eligible to work in Australia.

To be successful you will demonstrate your passion to make a difference in the lives of our residents and to work with them to ensure they receive the highest possible care, tailored to their needs and preferences.

Applications Close:
Sunday 2nd June 2019

Please apply with your current Resume and a cover letter with a summary of why this is the role for you.

If you feel this is the right role for you, don't wait, apply now!

Join a supportive and inclusive team environment

An opportunity to work within a growing organisation

Increase your take home pay with salary packaging opportunities

Ongoing learning and development opportunities
```

About Us:

Retail Safari
as part of 
CPM Australia
is a dynamic and innovative field marketing services agency offering its clients effective customer contact through a diverse range of channels including local area marketing, merchandising, assisted selling, mystery shopping, demonstration and brand activation.

About the Role:

Reporting to the Senior Account Manager, you will be primarily responsible for the delivery of daily support functions working closely with our Management and Operations Team to ensure field programs are successfully executed, delivered on time and maintained to our quality standards.

Key responsibilities may include but not be limited to: Client service contact, management and coordination of national POS distribution, management of tactical merchandising campaigns, management of timesheets and work schedules, generation of ad-hoc reports and insights, support and management of small and large scale training events daily communication with state managers and other stakeholders, coordination of training and recruitment processes, maintaining field communication channels and other ad-hoc tasks. About You:

Ideally we are looking for a candidate to ‘hit the ground running’ who has the confidence to take charge in this dynamic and diverse role:

Previous administrative and project coordination experience

A passionate and engaging personality is a must to be successful

Time management and ability to meet deadlines

Exceptional communication and organisational skills with strong attention to detail

Experience working with some form of CRMs

Ability to manipulate and interpret raw data to create usable and insightful reports and presentations.

Proficient level of PowerPoint and Word.

Ability to work both autonomously and collaboratively within a team

Previous customer/client service experience

About the Offer:

In return you will be rewarded with the opportunity to work with Australia’s 
LEADING 
Marketing Agency alongside global brads! Some of the other benefits of joining our team include:

An attractive remuneration package

Ongoing training and development opportunities (internal & external)

“Mates rates” with some of our corporate partnerships (mobile/internet, gas/electricity, white goods,  private health etc)

Health and Wellbeing Scheme – CPM contributing annually to either your gym membership, a hobby, evening class etc

Friday afternoon social gatherings

This will be a 12-month commitment with a strong potential to extend into a career opportunity or possible prospects on other leading programs.

If you are ready for a challenge and seek a rewarding career then this is not an opportunity to be missed – 
APPLY ONLINE NOW!

All candidates are encouraged to visit our website www.retailsafari.com.au and

```
About Us:

Retail Safari
as part of 
CPM Australia
is a dynamic and innovative field marketing services agency offering its clients effective customer contact through a diverse range of channels including local area marketing, merchandising, assisted selling, mystery shopping, demonstration and brand activation.

About the Role:

Reporting to the Senior Account Manager, you will be primarily responsible for the delivery of daily support functions working closely with our Management and Operations Team to ensure field programs are successfully executed, delivered on time and maintained to our quality standards.

Key responsibilities may include but not be limited to: Client service contact, management and coordination of national POS distribution, management of tactical merchandising campaigns, management of timesheets and work schedules, generation of ad-hoc reports and insights, support and management of small and large scale training events daily communication with state managers and other stakeholders, coordination of training and recruitment processes, maintaining field communication channels and other ad-hoc tasks. This is a key role with great client exposure, with room to grow and develop your retail marketing skills.

About You:

Ideally we are looking for a candidate to ‘hit the ground running’ who has the confidence to take charge in this dynamic and diverse role:

Previous administrative and project coordination experience

A passionate and engaging personality is a must to be successful

Time management and ability to meet deadlines

Exceptional communication and organisational skills with strong attention to detail

Experience working with some form of CRMs

Ability to manipulate and interpret raw data to create usable and insightful reports and presentations.

Proficient level of PowerPoint and Word.

Ability to work both autonomously and collaboratively within a team

Previous customer/client service experience

About the Offer:

In return you will be rewarded with the opportunity to work with Australia’s 
LEADING 
Marketing Agency alongside global brads! Some of the other benefits of joining our team include:

An attractive remuneration package

Ongoing training and development opportunities (internal & external)

“Mates rates” with some of our corporate partnerships (mobile/internet, gas/electricity, white goods,  private health etc)

Health and Wellbeing Scheme – CPM contributing annually to either your gym membership, a hobby, evening class etc

Friday afternoon social gatherings

This will be a 12-month commitment with a strong potential to extend into a career opportunity or possible prospects on other leading programs.

If you are ready for a challenge and seek a rewarding career then this is not an opportunity to be missed – 
APPLY ONLINE NOW!

All candidates are encouraged to visit our website www.retailsafari.com.au and

www.cpm-aus.com.au and before applying.

- Extract the raw context of the job advertisement.

The Company:

We are currently working in partnership with a commercial builder based in the Central coast who are looking for a Site Manager to join their experienced team. Over the past 4 years they have grown from strength to strength increasing their staff size from 5 people to 30. Their origins lies in the fast-paced retail market with their average project valued between $500K-2m, however over the past 2 years they have developed their client base to pick up larger new build projects valued up to $10m and work across a variety of sectors including health, education and residential sectors up to the value of $10m.

The Role:

Due to an increase in the size and number of projects they have taken the decision to bring on an extra Site Manager. You will be responsible for running your site making sure that all work is being carried out by trades to the programme provided by your project manager..

Experience:
The ideal candidate will have the following experience

Working to tight programmes

Able to lead a team and drive team

Have experience delivering retail projects, commercial project will also be considered.

Have stability on your CV

Able to work in team environment

Able to lead from the front

Be well presented and a good communicator to clients and sub-contractors

Company Culture: 
Become part of a fast paced, forward thinking company that looks after its staff. The companies’ directors come from larger scale commercial companies and they don’t want their company to take on an atmosphere where the employee doesn’t come first. They truly have a focus on providing their candidates with a good work life balance.

Benefits.
With the directors focus on work life balance they offer the following bonuses to ensure their staff are happy

- 6 weeks holiday as standard

- Full package offered including car, fuel and bonuses

- Package offered ranging from $100K-$140K dependant on experience levels

If this sounds like it could be the job you’ve been looking for and you would like more information, drop me an email on john.ainge@cgcrecruitment.com or call John Ainge on 0400 516 014.

Raw Job Advertisement Text**  
```
The Company:

We are currently working in partnership with a commercial builder based in the Central coast who are looking for a Site Manager to join their experienced team. Over the past 4 years they have grown from strength to strength increasing their staff size from 5 people to 30. Their origins lies in the fast-paced retail market with their average project valued between $500K-2m, however over the past 2 years they have developed their client base to pick up larger new build projects valued up to $10m and work across a variety of sectors including health, education and residential sectors up to the value of $10m.

The Role:

Due to an increase in the size and number of projects they have taken the decision to bring on an extra Site Manager. You will be responsible for running your site making sure that all work is being carried out by trades to the programme provided by your project manager..

Experience:
The ideal candidate will have the following experience

Working to tight programmes

Able to lead a team and drive team

Have experience delivering retail projects, commercial project will also be considered.

Have stability on your CV

Able to work in team environment

Able to lead from the front

Be well presented and a good communicator to clients and sub-contractors

Company Culture: 
Become part of a fast paced, forward thinking company that looks after its staff. The companies’ directors come from larger scale commercial companies and they don’t want their company to take on an atmosphere where the employee doesn’t come first. They truly have a focus on providing their candidates with a good work life balance.

Benefits.
With the directors focus on work life balance they offer the following bonuses to ensure their staff are happy

- 6 weeks holiday as standard

- Full package offered including car, fuel and bonuses

- Package offered ranging from $100K-$140K dependant on experience levels

If this sounds like it could be the job you’ve been looking for and you would like more information, drop me an email on john.ainge@cgcrecruitment.com or call John Ainge on 0400 516 014.
```
