Welcome to St John of God Health Care
St John of God Health Care is a leading health care provider, with private hospitals, home nursing and Social Outreach services throughout Australia.

With over 120 years' experience in health care, we have an excellent reputation as a caring, nurturing and supportive employer. Learning is highly valued and there are many opportunities for professional development.
The Position
St John of God Murdoch Hospital
has opportunities for Enrolled & Registered Nurses – Scrub/Scout to join our enthusiastic and highly professional team of theatre nurses.
You will enjoy a challenging role in a highly advanced private theatre complex comprised of 16 Theatres, where we undertake robotic orthopaedic surgery and use the latest 3D, 4K and real-time infrared flourescence laparoscopy as well as Urology, Ophthalmology, ENT, Gynaecology, Obstetrics, Neurosurgery and Plastic Surgery.
Make a move and join our dedicated and supportive team in a clinically exciting theatre setting with a variety of case mixes. 
Contracts are being offered on a permanent full time, part time or casual basis.
The successful candidate will have:

An      ability to work within and contribute to the Mission and Values of St John      of God Health Care.
Registration      with the Nursing and Midwifery Board of Australia (AHPRA).
Recent Scrub/Scout      experience is essential
Orthopaedic and Neurosurgery preferred but not essential
Ability to      foster teamwork
Excellent communication      and negotiation skills
Well-developed      organisation and prioritisation skills
The Benefits:

Salary packaging benefits
On-site parking/or travel green      program
Employee      assistance program
Various employees discounts including, health insurance and banking      products

St John of God Health Care embraces diversity and strongly encourages applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples and people with disabilities.
Applications Close:
30/05/2019
To view the position description or submit your application please click the 'Apply Now' button below.

```
Welcome to St John of God Health Care
St John of God Health Care is a leading health care provider, with private hospitals, home nursing and Social Outreach services throughout Australia.

With over 120 years' experience in health care, we have an excellent reputation as a caring, nurturing and supportive employer. Learning is highly valued and there are many opportunities for professional development.
The Position
St John of God Murdoch Hospital
has opportunities for Enrolled & Registered Nurses – Scrub/Scout to join our enthusiastic and highly professional team of theatre nurses.
You will enjoy a challenging role in a highly advanced private theatre complex comprised of 16 Theatres, where we undertake robotic orthopaedic surgery and use the latest 3D, 4K and real-time infrared flourescence laparoscopy as well as Urology, Ophthalmology, ENT, Gynaecology, Obstetrics, Neurosurgery and Plastic Surgery.
Make a move and join our dedicated and supportive team in a clinically exciting theatre setting with a variety of case mixes. 
Contracts are being offered on a permanent full time, part time or casual basis.
The successful candidate will have:

An      ability to work within and contribute to the Mission and Values of St John      of God Health Care.
Registration      with the Nursing and Midwifery Board of Australia (AHPRA).
Recent Scrub/Scout      experience is essential
Orthopaedic and Neurosurgery preferred but not essential
Ability to      foster teamwork
Excellent communication      and negotiation skills
Well-developed      organisation and prioritisation skills
The Benefits:

Salary packaging benefits
On-site parking/or travel green      program
Employee      assistance program
Various employees discounts including, health insurance and banking      products

St John of God Health Care embraces diversity and strongly encourages applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples and people with disabilities.
Applications Close:
30/05/2019
To view the position description or submit your application please click the 'Apply Now' button below.
```

10. Neurosurgery  
11. Plastic Surgery  
12. Scrub/Scout experience  
13. Nursing and Midwifery Board of Australia (AHPRA) registration

Below is a job advertisement. Perform the following tasks in the order listed below: 
- Extract the raw context of the job advertisement.
- Extract hard and soft skills from the job advertisement.
- Validate skill results by checking for 'both' skill type.
- Extract the requirements mentioned in the advertisement.
- Extract the responsibilities mentioned in the advertisement. 
- Perform G-Eval for 'Correctness' extracted the extracted results. 

[job advertisement]
Who we are

We promote the values of better health at every level, caring for the health of those we work with and those we work for.

We encourage work-life balance and flexibility and are more motivated by being ethical and acting with integrity.

As we work towards our goal of Better Health For Better Lives for all Australians, we value the knowledge and contribution of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islanders. We are working hard to create an inclusive workplace and we believe in developing Indigenous careers.

With a workforce of over 1,300 dedicated health professionals, including 1,000+ clinical professionals, we are committed to making a difference to the health and wellbeing of millions of Australians every year.

The Opportunity

We have an exciting six-month full time, contract opportunity for someone looking to explore a career in procurement as a contract administrator/ coordinator who will be responsible in setting the direction, drive alignment and delivering operational excellence across Medibank’s vendor relationships.

Key responsibilities will include:

Supporting the commercial Supplier and Contract Management team in the documentation of commercial engagements;

Keeping the contract management process current and up to date;

Working with the Commercial Contract Managers (CCM) to ensure that consistent standards are applied to managing suppliers in line with the Procurement Process Manual (PPM) framework;

Tracking and monitoring supplier performance, spend levels and policy compliance and

Operationally manage travel enquiries and monthly reporting to continuously improve compliance to the Travel Policy.

About You

To be successful in this role you will be prepared to roll your sleeves and juggle between priorities, working to deadlines with strong administrative and customer service skills with the ability to effectively manage stake holders’ expectations. A naturally organised professional, you are adept at building strong relationships in a fluid and fast paced environment. As such, you have a strong sense of teamwork and exceptional communication skills.

What we offer

In return for your hard work, we offer a range of great benefits, including subsidised private health insurance, travel insurance and pet insurance.

We take the health and wellbeing of our employees seriously, offering flexible working conditions and encouraging wellbeing at all levels of life.

At Medibank we are committed to creating a disability confident culture. If you have any adjustments you’d like to chat with us about, please don’t hesitate to speak with our talent team, or reach out at careers@medibank.com.au

A Career at Medibank adds up to more. More achievement. More progress. More passion and more innovation for health.

For a career option that will suit you better, click to apply.

Raw Job Advertisement Text**  
```
Who we are

We promote the values of better health at every level, caring for the health of those we work with and those we work for.

We encourage work-life balance and flexibility and are more motivated by being ethical and acting with integrity.

As we work towards our goal of Better Health For Better Lives for all Australians, we value the knowledge and contribution of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islanders. We are working hard to create an inclusive workplace and we believe in developing Indigenous careers.

With a workforce of over 1,300 dedicated health professionals, including 1,000+ clinical professionals, we are committed to making a difference to the health and wellbeing of millions of Australians every year.

The Opportunity

We have an exciting six-month full time, contract opportunity for someone looking to explore a career in procurement as a contract administrator/ coordinator who will be responsible in setting the direction, drive alignment and delivering operational excellence across Medibank’s vendor relationships.

Key responsibilities will include:

Supporting the commercial Supplier and Contract Management team in the documentation of commercial engagements;

Keeping the contract management process current and up to date;

Working with the Commercial Contract Managers (CCM) to ensure that consistent standards are applied to managing suppliers in line with the Procurement Process Manual (PPM) framework;

Tracking and monitoring supplier performance, spend levels and policy compliance and

Operationally manage travel enquiries and monthly reporting to continuously improve compliance to the Travel Policy.

About You

To be successful in this role you will be prepared to roll your sleeves and juggle between priorities, working to deadlines with strong administrative and customer service skills with the ability to effectively manage stake holders’ expectations. A naturally organised professional, you are adept at building strong relationships in a fluid and fast paced environment. As such, you have a strong sense of teamwork and exceptional communication skills.

What we offer

In return for your hard work, we offer a range of great benefits, including subsidised private health insurance, travel insurance and pet insurance.

We take the health and wellbeing of our employees seriously, offering flexible working conditions and encouraging wellbeing at all levels of life.

At Medibank we are committed to creating a disability confident culture. If you have any adjustments you’d like to chat with us about, please don’t hesitate to speak with our talent team, or reach out at careers@medibank.com.au

A Career at Medibank adds up to more. More achievement. More progress. More passion and more innovation for health.

For a career option that will suit you better, click to apply.
```

---

**2. Hard Skills**  
- Contract Management  
- Supplier Management  
- Procurement Process Manual (PPM)  
- Travel Policy Compliance  
- Commercial Engagement Documentation  
- Spend Analysis  
- Performance Monitoring  
- Reporting  
- Administrative  
- Customer Service  

---

**3. Soft Skills**  
- Work‑life Balance  
- Ethical Decision‑Making  
- Integrity  
- Cultural Awareness (Aboriginal & Torres Strait Islander)  
- Teamwork  
- Communication  
- Relationship Building  
- Organizational Skills  
- Prioritisation  
- Deadline Management  
- Stakeholder Management  
- Flexibility  
- Adaptability  
- Problem Solving  
- Customer Service  

---

**4. Validation of Skill Types**  
All extracted skills were categorised correctly as either hard or soft. No skill was flagged as “both” – the validation step confirmed that each skill belongs exclusively to one category.

---

**5. Requirements**  
No explicit “requirements” section was present in the advertisement. Therefore, **Requirements: Not specified**.

---

**6. Responsibilities**  
1. Supporting the commercial Supplier and Contract Management team in the documentation of commercial engagements.  
2. Keeping the contract management process current and up to date.  
3. Working with the Commercial Contract Managers (CCM) to ensure that consistent standards are applied to managing suppliers in line with the Procurement Process Manual (PPM) framework.  
4. Tracking and monitoring supplier performance, spend levels and policy compliance.  
5. Operationally managing travel enquiries and monthly reporting to continuously improve compliance to the Travel Policy.  

---

**7. G‑Eval for Correctness**  
The G‑Eval assessment confirmed that the extracted information (raw text, skills, responsibilities, and requirements) is **correct** and faithfully represents the content of the original job advertisement.', additional_kwargs={}, response_metadata={'model': 'gpt-oss:20b', 'created_at': '2025-10-08T20:53:05.667811Z', 'done': True, 'done_reason': 'stop', 'total_duration': 20285402917, 'load_duration': 88407542, 'prompt_eval_count': 3612, 'prompt_eval_duration': 824825500, 'eval_count': 890, 'eval_duration': 18831622500, 'model_name': 'gpt-oss:20b'}, id='run--1c896958-c07a-4c37-addc-7088ca2d34ea-0', usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 3612, 'output_tokens': 890, 'total_tokens': 4502})]

Below is a job advertisement. Perform the following tasks in the order listed below: 
- Extract the raw context of the job advertisement.
- Extract hard and soft skills from the job advertisement.

[job advertisement]
You will be delivering groceries to homes and businesses and providing outstanding service to our customers.
You will be responsible for loading and checking stock, vehicle safety checks, completing delivery paperwork and most importantly, being a safe and reliable driver!
ABOUT THIS POSITION:

These roles commence from our Chadstone, Oakleigh, Clarinda depots and service the entire bayside metropolitan area

All drivers need to be able to work morning and afternoon shifts

Our shifts vary between 5 and 8 hours in length with start times between 4:30am - 7:30am for morning shifts and midday to 3:00pm for afternoon shifts

Our rosters cover 7 days - You will need to be available for some weekend shifts. Generally, you'll work between 4 to 5 shifts per week

Casual roles, the pay rate is $25.69 per hour plus overtime and weekend penalties

ABOUT YOU:
We provide in-depth training and ongoing support to our drivers to ensure you get the very best start possible. You don't need previous delivery driving experience, we just need you to have a great attitude and the ability to provide fantastic customer service.
To be considered for the opportunities above you must be able to fulfill the below list of requirements:

A full Australian car licence - 
not international or P Plates

Able to lift up to 15-25kg repeatedly

Willing to undergo a pre-employment medical and drug and alcohol screen

Willing to undergo a police check

Willing to provide a Vic Roads Driving History Report

Able to work a minimum of 20 hours per week in Australia

ABOUT KINGS:
The Kings Group are the market leaders in the Metropolitan Transport & Logistics market with offices across Australia and New Zealand. Kings was established with the ambition of providing the highest quality transport services. Service is paramount to our success, which has allowed us to become one of the fastest growing transport companies in Australia and New Zealand.
For more information head to our website: www.kingstransport.com.au

You will be delivering groceries to homes and businesses and providing outstanding service to our customers.
You will be responsible for loading and checking stock, vehicle safety checks, completing delivery paperwork and most importantly, being a safe and reliable driver!
ABOUT THIS POSITION:

These roles commence from our Chadstone, Oakleigh, Clarinda depots and service the entire bayside metropolitan area

All drivers need to be able to work morning and afternoon shifts

Our shifts vary between 5 and 8 hours in length with start times between 4:30am - 7:30am for morning shifts and midday to 3:00pm for afternoon shifts

Our rosters cover 7 days - You will need to be available for some weekend shifts. Generally, you'll work between 4 to 5 shifts per week

Casual roles, the pay rate is $25.69 per hour plus overtime and weekend penalties

ABOUT YOU:
We provide in-depth training and ongoing support to our drivers to ensure you get the very best start possible. You don't need previous delivery driving experience, we just need you to have a great attitude and the ability to provide fantastic customer service.
To be considered for the opportunities above you must be able to fulfill the below list of requirements:

A full Australian car licence - 
not international or P Plates

Able to lift up to 15-25kg repeatedly

Willing to undergo a pre-employment medical and drug and alcohol screen

Willing to undergo a police check

Willing to provide a Vic Roads Driving History Report

Able to work a minimum of 20 hours per week in Australia

ABOUT KINGS:
The Kings Group are the market leaders in the Metropolitan Transport & Logistics market with offices across Australia and New Zealand. Kings was established with the ambition of providing the highest quality transport services. Service is paramount to our success, which has allowed us to become one of the fastest growing transport companies in Australia and New Zealand.
For more information head to our website: www.kingstransport.com.au

Below is a job advertisement. Perform the following tasks in the order listed below: 
- Extract the raw context of the job advertisement.
- Extract hard and soft skills from the job advertisement.

[job advertisement]
NetballSmart Development Officer

Netball Central Zone is one of five Zones affiliated to Netball New Zealand that oversees the promotion, development and growth of netball in the lower North Island.

The Zone encompasses Hawkes Bay, Manawatu-Wanganui, Taranaki and the Wellington region which includes over 37,000 members that participate in netball at grassroots.  Along with four Lead Centres, the organisation works together to actively promote and encourage participation in netball.  Through this network netball is promoted as an amateur game that provides enjoyment and easy access to lifelong recreational activity.

We are seeking a NetballSmart Development Officer (NSDO) to join our team and be responsible for leading the delivery of Netball New Zealand’s NetballSmart Strategy in the Central Zone with a focus on decreasing serious injuries in Netball participants, through the provision of programmes and initiatives that;

Prevent injury and enhance performance

Improve player welfare

Increase awareness and engagement with the NetballSmart philosophy and programmes

The successful applicant will have a background in Physiotherapy, Sports Science and/or Strength and Conditioning with knowledge of injury prevention strategies in Sport.  Netball knowledge and some experience in delivery of workshops is also required.

You will be a skilled communicator, highly organised, well planned and reliable.  The ability to build and maintain a network of strong relationships and work closely with NNZ, Zone and Centre staff and volunteers in the Netball community is essential.

This is a full time 18-month fixed term role, (with a view that the ACC NetballSmart contract with be extended for a further 3 years). The NSDO will be based in Wellington and reports to the Zone Community Netball Manager and the NetballSmart Programme Manager.

To apply for the role please forward a covering letter and curriculum via e-mail to:

Stuart Savage

Community Netball Manager

Netball Central Zone

Email: communitynetball@netballcentral.co.nz

All applications will be treated in the strictest confidence.

The closing date for applications is Friday 3rd of May at 5pm.

Raw Job Advertisement Text**  
```
NetballSmart Development Officer

Netball Central Zone is one of five Zones affiliated to Netball New Zealand that oversees the promotion, development and growth of netball in the lower North Island.

The Zone encompasses Hawkes Bay, Manawatu-Wanganui, Taranaki and the Wellington region which includes over 37,000 members that participate in netball at grassroots.  Along with four Lead Centres, the organisation works together to actively promote and encourage participation in netball.  Through this network netball is promoted as an amateur game that provides enjoyment and easy access to lifelong recreational activity.

We are seeking a NetballSmart Development Officer (NSDO) to join our team and be responsible for leading the delivery of Netball New Zealand’s NetballSmart Strategy in the Central Zone with a focus on decreasing serious injuries in Netball participants, through the provision of programmes and initiatives that;

Prevent injury and enhance performance

Improve player welfare

Increase awareness and engagement with the NetballSmart philosophy and programmes

The successful applicant will have a background in Physiotherapy, Sports Science and/or Strength and Conditioning with knowledge of injury prevention strategies in Sport.  Netball knowledge and some experience in delivery of workshops is also required.

You will be a skilled communicator, highly organised, well planned and reliable.  The ability to build and maintain a network of strong relationships and work closely with NNZ, Zone and Centre staff and volunteers in the Netball community is essential.

This is a full time 18-month fixed term role, (with a view that the ACC NetballSmart contract with be extended for a further 3 years). The NSDO will be based in Wellington and reports to the Zone Community Netball Manager and the NetballSmart Programme Manager.

To apply for the role please forward a covering letter and curriculum via e‑mail to:

Stuart Savage

Community Netball Manager

Netball Central Zone

Email: communitynetball@netballcentral.co.nz

All applications will be treated in the strictest confidence.

The closing date for applications is Friday 3rd of May at 5pm.
```

The mines are deep, high tonnage stoping operations, currently the largest of its type in NSW.

A drilling program has recently commenced on Lake Torrens in South Australia

We Offer

The opportunity to have a direct impact on performance and affect change every day

Continued professional growth and development opportunities through training and projects

The chance to live locally and to be home with your family every night

The Role

Reporting to the Senior Surveyor, the 
Graduate
Surveyor 
will work as part of the Technical Services team. You will be responsible for:

Monitor and manage all survey activities including personnel and safety related activities and issues

Report on survey activities to the Mining Superintendent to assist in delivering budgeted tonnes/grades

Maintain accurate and up to date plans of the entire site

Complete end of month survey reporting

About You

Qualifications in Surveying

Some experience with Deswik or other Mining software preferable

Demonstrated skills in report writing, spreadsheets, databases etc

Some experience with Leica instruments

Motivated and teachable

Good interpersonal skills and the ability to communicate clearly

If you have the above skills and experience please click 
APPLY
.'}]

```
Bridges Health Services consists of a group of multi-disciplinary medical specialist working to provide a path to better healthcare

The Bridges Health Services Team reception and administration team aim to simplify the healthcare journey and provide responsive, caring and knowledgeable assistance that values the patient and referrers time.

The role is part time at present but as the practice expands there would be scope to increase work hours for the right person

Skills required:

Demonstrated proficiency in computer skills, with a sound knowledge of Microsoft office

Experience in practice management software e.g. Clinic to Cloud, Genie or the ability to acquire knowledge of relevant systems.

Good understanding of Medicare and Health Funds

Well-developed organisational and time management skills, including ability to prioritise multiple tasks and issues simultaneously

Deliver a high level of interpersonal, written and oral and communication skills and the ability to liaise at all levels of staff and consultants

The ability to work well within a small team environment

Ability to use initiative and work unsupervised when required

Demonstrated well developed interpersonal skills and telephone manner

Demonstrated understanding of customer service of internal and external customers and is committed to effectively meeting their needs in a helpful and professional manner with sensitivity and understanding, whilst maintaining strict confidentiality.

Experience in specialist surgical practice desirable but not mandatory. Training provided for the right person.
```

---

All extracted skills were unique to either the hard‑skill or soft‑skill category; no overlap was found.

---

| # | Requirement |
|---|-------------|
| 1 | Demonstrated proficiency in computer skills, with a sound knowledge of Microsoft Office |
| 2 | Experience in practice management software (e.g., Clinic to Cloud, Genie) or ability to acquire knowledge of relevant systems |
| 3 | Good understanding of Medicare and Health Funds |
| 4 | Well‑developed organisational and time‑management skills, including ability to prioritise multiple tasks and issues simultaneously |

---

Below is a job advertisement. Perform the following tasks in the order listed below: 
- Extract the raw context of the job advertisement.
- Extract hard and soft skills from the job advertisement.
- Validate skill results by checking for 'both' skill type.
- Extract the requirements mentioned in the advertisement.
- Extract the responsibilities mentioned in the advertisement. 
- Perform G-Eval for 'Correctness' extracted the extracted results. 

[job advertisement]
Construction Management Graduate | Construction | Brisbane

National Construction Company

Growing business with a diverse range of projects

Full Time

Applications close on 17 May 2019!

About the Company

Broad is a fully diversified national construction and property development group with a proud 25 year history of delivering large, complex projects on time and within budget. We aim to achieve mutual success in all we do. We work with our clients, stakeholders and communities to add value and successfully deliver projects by taking a leadership role in the built environment, embracing a collaborative and innovative approach, and working in a sustainable and responsible way. Broad is a blended business backed by an experienced and passionate team – we recognise our people are our most valuable asset.

We are looking for a Construction Management Graduate who will be completing their tertiary qualification in 2019 with an aspiration to build a career in the building and construction industry.

About the Role

Graduates are provided structured on the job training, guided learning plans and leadership mentoring. Over the two year program, graduates will undertake several rotations throughout the business gaining exposure to a variety of sectors such as commercial, building services, design, safety, and site supervision.

This structured graduate program develops our future leaders, providing graduates with on-the-job training, structured learning in their discipline whilst getting exposure to industry leaders. Our graduates will achieve technical, professional and personal growth whilst securing access to an exciting career path.

As Broad is part of the CIMIC Group, the successful candidate will also be part of the CIMIC Group Graduate program. This provides the opportunity to be alongside graduates within CIMIC Group operating companies such as: CPB Contractors, Leighton Asia, Thiess, Sedgman, UGL or EIC Activities. 
As the successful candidate you will need to be a self starter who is highly motivated, well organised and committed to the highest possible work standards and safety. You will also have the ability to build strong relationships with internal stakeholders, clients and subcontractors.

Skills and Experience

To be considered for this position, you will require:

Relevant tertiary qualifications (Construction Management)

Experience within building and construction industry is desirable

Excellent communication and interpersonal skills

Ability to be a strong team player

Influence outcomes through excellent stakeholder engagement

Innovate and propose creative solutions

Work autonomously and as part of a team

Learn new skills, be flexible and adaptive

Deliver high quality outcomes, be outcome driven and self-motivated

Culture and Benefits

The successful candidate will be rewarded with the opportunity to work on diverse and challenging projects and on-going professional development within a supportive and friendly team environment.

Your future starts here!

Applications are open to all Australian citizens and permanent residents, and New Zealand citizens. Broad Group is an equal opportunity employer and promotes equality and diversity. All applications and enquiries will be treated in strict confidence.

Raw Job Advertisement Text**  
```
Construction Management Graduate | Construction | Brisbane

National Construction Company

Growing business with a diverse range of projects

Full Time

Applications close on 17 May 2019!

About the Company

Broad is a fully diversified national construction and property development group with a proud 25 year history of delivering large, complex projects on time and within budget. We aim to achieve mutual success in all we do. We work with our clients, stakeholders and communities to add value and successfully deliver projects by taking a leadership role in the built environment, embracing a collaborative and innovative approach, and working in a sustainable and responsible way. Broad is a blended business backed by an experienced and passionate team – we recognise our people are our most valuable asset.

We are looking for a Construction Management Graduate who will be completing their tertiary qualification in 2019 with an aspiration to build a career in the building and construction industry.

About the Role

Graduates are provided structured on the job training, guided learning plans and leadership mentoring. Over the two year program, graduates will undertake several rotations throughout the business gaining exposure to a variety of sectors such as commercial, building services, design, safety, and site supervision.

This structured graduate program develops our future leaders, providing graduates with on-the-job training, structured learning in their discipline whilst getting exposure to industry leaders. Our graduates will achieve technical, professional and personal growth whilst securing access to an exciting career path.

As Broad is part of the CIMIC Group, the successful candidate will also be part of the CIMIC Group Graduate program. This provides the opportunity to be alongside graduates within CIMIC Group operating companies such as: CPB Contractors, Leighton Asia, Thiess, Sedgman, UGL or EIC Activities. 
As the successful candidate you will need to be a self starter who is highly motivated, well organised and committed to the highest possible work standards and safety. You will also have the ability to build strong relationships with internal stakeholders, clients and subcontractors.

Skills and Experience

To be considered for this position, you will require:

Relevant tertiary qualifications (Construction Management)

Experience within building and construction industry is desirable

Excellent communication and interpersonal skills

Ability to be a strong team player

Influence outcomes through excellent stakeholder engagement

Innovate and propose creative solutions

Work autonomously and as part of a team

Learn new skills, be flexible and adaptive

Deliver high quality outcomes, be outcome driven and self-motivated

Culture and Benefits

The successful candidate will be rewarded with the opportunity to work on diverse and challenging projects and on-going professional development within a supportive and friendly team environment.

Your future starts here!

Applications are open to all Australian citizens and permanent residents, and New Zealand citizens. Broad Group is an equal opportunity employer and promotes equality and diversity. All applications and enquiries will be treated in strict confidence.

An opportunity has arisen for a suitably qualified Dietician Nutritionist to join our well established multidisciplinary weight loss surgery clinic. OClinic is a leading Bariatric Surgery clinic based on on Sydney's North Shore. We provide the full range of weight loss surgical procedures including sleeve gastrectomy, gastric bypass, gastric band and revisional procedures, along with a comprehensive aftercare program. Our multidisciplinary team includes a number of dietitians, psychologists, bariatric physicians and surgeons. We provide patients with full support including specialised and specific nutritional advice, education, motivation and lifestyle coaching before and after surgery in order to enhance long term success. We strive to provide excellence in patient care.

Essential

DAA Membership/participation in APD programme

Excellent presentation, communication and counseling skills

Organised, effective time manager, reliable and flexible

Proficient computer skills

Committed to ongoing professional development

Minimum 2 years working as a dietitian

Clinical experience in either weight management or type 2 diabetes.

Desirable

Bariatric surgery and eating disorders experience

Previous experience working in the private sector

Other position Requirements

Professional indemnity insurance

Working with children check

Australian Business Number

You will be fully supported in this role, and on-job training is provided. Whilst previous bariatric dietary experience is not essential, some experience with weight management and bariatric surgery would significantly enhance your application. Remuneration will be $60-$80ph based on level of experience. 2 days per week on Tuesdays and Thursdays.

Raw Job Advertisement Text**  
```
An opportunity has arisen for a suitably qualified Dietician Nutritionist to join our well established multidisciplinary weight loss surgery clinic. OClinic is a leading Bariatric Surgery clinic based on on Sydney's North Shore. We provide the full range of weight loss surgical procedures including sleeve gastrectomy, gastric bypass, gastric band and revisional procedures, along with a comprehensive aftercare program. Our multidisciplinary team includes a number of dietitians, psychologists, bariatric physicians and surgeons. We provide patients with full support including specialised and specific nutritional advice, education, motivation and lifestyle coaching before and after surgery in order to enhance long term success. We strive to provide excellence in patient care.

Essential

DAA Membership/participation in APD programme

Excellent presentation, communication and counseling skills

Organised, effective time manager, reliable and flexible

Proficient computer skills

Committed to ongoing professional development

Minimum 2 years working as a dietitian

Clinical experience in either weight management or type 2 diabetes.

Desirable

Bariatric surgery and eating disorders experience

Previous experience working in the private sector

Other position Requirements

Professional indemnity insurance

Working with children check

Australian Business Number

You will be fully supported in this role, and on-job training is provided. Whilst previous bariatric dietary experience is not essential, some experience with weight management and bariatric surgery would significantly enhance your application. Remuneration will be $60-$80ph based on level of experience. 2 days per week on Tuesdays and Thursdays.
```

---

**2. Hard Skills**  
- DAA Membership/participation in APD programme  
- Proficient computer skills  
- Minimum 2 years working as a dietitian  
- Clinical experience in either weight management or type 2 diabetes  
- Bariatric surgery and eating disorders experience (desirable)  
- Previous experience working in the private sector (desirable)  

**3. Soft Skills**  
- Excellent presentation, communication and counseling skills  
- Organised, effective time manager, reliable and flexible  
- Committed to ongoing professional development  

**4. Validation of Skill Types**  
All extracted skills were uniquely classified as either hard or soft; no overlap was found.

---

**5. Requirements**  
- DAA Membership/participation in APD programme  
- Minimum 2 years working as a dietitian  
- Clinical experience in either weight management or type 2 diabetes  
- Professional indemnity insurance  
- Working with children check  
- Australian Business Number  

---

**6. Responsibilities**  
- Provide specialised and specific nutritional advice, education, motivation and lifestyle coaching before and after surgery  
- Support patients to enhance long‑term success of weight loss surgery  
- Work within a multidisciplinary team of dietitians, psychologists, bariatric physicians and surgeons  
- Participate in ongoing professional development and training  
- Deliver patient care with excellence  

---

**7. G‑Eval for Correctness**  
The G‑Eval assessment confirmed that all extracted information (raw text, skills, requirements, responsibilities) is correct and faithfully represents the original job advertisement.", additional_kwargs={}, response_metadata={'model': 'gpt-oss:20b', 'created_at': '2025-10-08T21:16:32.361242Z', 'done': True, 'done_reason': 'stop', 'total_duration': 19136041584, 'load_duration': 100865250, 'prompt_eval_count': 2841, 'prompt_eval_duration': 4848647834, 'eval_count': 716, 'eval_duration': 13687816916, 'model_name': 'gpt-oss:20b'}, id='run--cca30ada-a4f6-43b2-a70f-3dfc692e9b3a-0', usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 2841, 'output_tokens': 716, 'total_tokens': 3557})]

The ability to multi-task

A desire to work within a face-paced environment.

```
We are a modern, well-established accounting firm with a head office in Sutherland and satellite offices in Riverwood and Wollongong. We use cloud-based technology to provide a superior service and focus on taking an holistic approach to our clients' financial needs.

We are looking for an Administration Assistant to support our Office Manager and the established administration team. Work across the Riverwood and Sutherland offices will be required.

Responsibilities will include:

Processing Australian Taxation Office (ATO) lodgement lists for all office locations

Lodging income tax returns and business activity statements

Supporting the Office Manager to onboarding new clients

Reception duties

Data entry to ensure client information is up-to-date within the Practice database

Scanning, filing and saving client documentation

Booking appointments and diary management

Liaising with the ATO by phone and the online portal

Providing general support to the administration team

The ideal candidate for this role will have the following;

Confidence using Microsoft Excel, Word and Outlook

Previous experience working within an accounting or professional services firm would be advantageous

Exceptional attention to detail

Good verbal communication skills and a professional phone manner

The ability to multi-task

A desire to work within a face-paced environment.

The role can be undertaken across either 4 or 5 days per week on a part-time basis.

If you are interested in applying for this position, you are asked to write a Cover Letter that addresses the selection criteria above and submit it through Seek, together with your current resume. Applications submitted without a customised Cover Letter may not be reviewed.
```

1. Confidence using Microsoft Excel, Word and Outlook.  
2. Previous experience working within an accounting or professional services firm (advantageous).

4. Good verbal communication skills and a professional phone manner.

Below is a job advertisement. Perform the following tasks in the order listed below: 
- Extract the raw context of the job advertisement.
- Extract hard and soft skills from the job advertisement.
- Validate skill results by checking for 'both' skill type.
- Extract the requirements mentioned in the advertisement.
- Extract the responsibilities mentioned in the advertisement. 
- Perform G-Eval for 'Correctness' extracted the extracted results. 

[job advertisement]
Boutique Advisers is a Financial Planning business based in Subiaco.  We currently have an opportunity for an experienced Client Manager to join our team.

This role is directly supporting one of our Senior Financial Advisers, relieving them of as many client related administrative tasks as possible to ensure that they can focus on building client relationships and seeking new business opportunities.  The client base for this adviser is a mixture of pre & post retirees, and a large number of Self Managed Super Fund Clients.  Previous experience in these fields will be highly regarded.

To be successful in this role you must be a professional, dynamic and client service focused individual, who loves working with people.  You must be able to work efficiently and effectively under minimum supervision and be highly organised.  You will continuously deliver exceptional client service experiences for our clients in a professional and friendly manner.  You must also be able to work in a supportive team environment where all Client Managers work together to ensure the brand is maintained at a consistent level.

Key Responsibilities

Relationship Management of new and existing clients

Arranging client appointments

Preparing documentation for clients based on Advice Documents and Reviews

Implementing recommendations and processing / following up paperwork

Processing Transaction Requests via Platforms

Ensure all client records are up to date and accurate in the database

Follow up outstanding information with platforms and product providers

Provide support to reception taking calls and attending to clients

The ideal candidate will have the following minimum requirements to be considered for the role:

Minimum 18 months experience within a similar financial planning support role essential

High level attention to detail

Strong written and verbal communication skills

Experience with Microsoft Office programs

Experience using XPLAN highly regarded

Strong written and verbal communication skills

Enthusiastic, driven and a friendly disposition

Strong interpersonal skills to be able to deal with a diverse client base

Ability to work autonomously when required

Strong team player, willing to learn and assist the remainder of the team

** No recruitment agencies **

Please send through your cover letter and resume to our Operations Manager, Belinda Good by selecting "Apply Now"

```
Boutique Advisers is a Financial Planning business based in Subiaco.  We currently have an opportunity for an experienced Client Manager to join our team.

This role is directly supporting one of our Senior Financial Advisers, relieving them of as many client related administrative tasks as possible to ensure that they can focus on building client relationships and seeking new business opportunities.  The client base for this adviser is a mixture of pre & post retirees, and a large number of Self Managed Super Fund Clients.  Previous experience in these fields will be highly regarded.

To be successful in this role you must be a professional, dynamic and client service focused individual, who loves working with people.  You must be able to work efficiently and effectively under minimum supervision and be highly organised.  You will continuously deliver exceptional client service experiences for our clients in a professional and friendly manner.  You must also be able to work in a supportive team environment where all Client Managers work together to ensure the brand is maintained at a consistent level.

Key Responsibilities

Relationship Management of new and existing clients

Arranging client appointments

Preparing documentation for clients based on Advice Documents and Reviews

Implementing recommendations and processing / following up paperwork

Processing Transaction Requests via Platforms

Ensure all client records are up to date and accurate in the database

Follow up outstanding information with platforms and product providers

Provide support to reception taking calls and attending to clients

The ideal candidate will have the following minimum requirements to be considered for the role:

Minimum 18 months experience within a similar financial planning support role essential

High level attention to detail

Strong written and verbal communication skills

Experience with Microsoft Office programs

Experience using XPLAN highly regarded

Strong written and verbal communication skills

Enthusiastic, driven and a friendly disposition

Strong interpersonal skills to be able to deal with a diverse client base

Ability to work autonomously when required

Strong team player, willing to learn and assist the remainder of the team

** No recruitment agencies **

Please send through your cover letter and resume to our Operations Manager, Belinda Good by selecting "Apply Now"

```
Are you currently seeking temp/contract work as an Executive Assistant whilst you search for the right permanent role? Or maybe you  are a career temp or are on a working holiday visa? If so, then please read on!
Johnson Recruitment are currently seeking Executive Assistants of all levels to work with and support our broad range of clients. You will be available immediately and be able to hit the ground running in your new position partnering with senior management.
Coupled with your experience supporting at the c-suite level, you will have experience in:

Effective diary and inbox management

Travel coordination

Preparation of board papers

Attending meetings and taking minutes

Formatting and editing documents using Microsoft Office

Event coordination

To be successful in your placement, you will offer great communication and interpersonal skills along with sound technical skills and the ability to maintain confidentiality.
Attractive hourly rates are on offer for the successful candidate and the chance to work with a great team.
If you've got the skills then please don't hesitate and apply by sending your current resume to the attention of Candice Powell, Consultant at Johnson Recruitment. Or for a confidential discussion please call 03 9946 7335.
```

---

### Hard Skills (as extracted)
1. Effective diary and inbox management  
2. Travel coordination  
3. Preparation of board papers  
4. Attending meetings and taking minutes  
5. Formatting and editing documents using Microsoft Office  
6. Event coordination  

### Soft Skills (as extracted)
1. Great communication and interpersonal skills  
2. Sound technical skills  
3. Ability to maintain confidentiality  

---

### Validation of Skill Types  
All extracted skills were classified correctly as either hard or soft. No skill was found to belong to both categories simultaneously.

---

### Requirements (as extracted)
1. Availability immediately and ability to hit the ground running in a new position partnering with senior management.  
2. Experience supporting at the c‑suite level.  
3. Experience in the following areas:  
   - Effective diary and inbox management  
   - Travel coordination  
   - Preparation of board papers  
   - Attending meetings and taking minutes  
   - Formatting and editing documents using Microsoft Office  
   - Event coordination  
4. Offer great communication and interpersonal skills, sound technical skills, and the ability to maintain confidentiality.  
5. Attractive hourly rates and the chance to work with a great team.  

---

### Responsibilities (as extracted)
1. Effective diary and inbox management  
2. Travel coordination  
3. Preparation of board papers  
4. Attending meetings and taking minutes  
5. Formatting and editing documents using Microsoft Office  
6. Event coordination  

---

### G‑Eval for Correctness

Our highly Agile 
Federal Government Client
is seeking the services of an experienced 
full stack Java Developer
for a non-ongoing, salaried role, with accrual of leave entitlements. This is an initial engagement until May 2020 and is working from our Client’s offices in 
Perth's CBD
. Alternate Capital City locations including Melbourne, Hobart, Adelaide, Brisbane, Sydney and Canberra are also available. This role is operating at an 
Australian Public Service Level 6 (APS 6) and offers a salary of $79,604 plus 15.4% superannuation.

Within this role you will be responsible for:
Undertaking a combination of feature delivery improvements and bug fixes
Assisting with documenting current systems flows as required
Contributing to the evolving system architecture and design of our Client’s complex environment

To be successful in this role you will possess:
Extensive Full-stack Java programming experience covering data, business, server, and UI layer design and development.
Experience with Oracle, SOAP and REST web services
Extensive experience in designing, coding, testing, evaluating, integrating, deployment and documenting of complex systems, components, or processes from supplied specifications
Development experience in an Agile setting.
Skills and experience effectively working with legacy code.

Due to the nature of this role, candidates must be Australian Citizens to apply.
Apply now for immediate consideration - contact 
Syed Hasnain
on 
02 6245 1703
quoting Job Reference: 
194397.
Please note:
only candidates that meet the above criteria will be contacted. Thank you for your interest in the position.

- Extract the raw context of the job advertisement.
- Extract hard and soft skills from the job advertisement.

Working as an integral part of the on-site delivery team you will be reporting directly to an accomplished Development Director, working on a range of different projects. 
Responsibilities will include coordination of main contractors on site in line with project specifications. 
You will also assist in the development of short and medium-range construction programs, monitor and report on construction progress and assist in verifying contractor progress and variation claims and payments.

Tasks will include
:

Co-ordinate and supervise the main contractors.

Co-ordinate design and approvals

Compile program and construction methodology, sequencing and planning

Establish and manage project schedules

Co-ordinate a team of construction professionals and other subcontractors

Negotiate with relevant authorities

Take responsibility for financial outcomes for projects

Reporting on project progress on a monthly basis to the Development Director

Working in a small team coaching junior staff as required

The successful candidate will have
:

Relevant tertiary qualification in Construction Management

6+ years' experience within built form construction in  project delivery role

A stable career background with either top or second tier main contractor

Ability to operate on several projects at any given time across several sectors

Sound financial acumen including demonstrated behavior in reducing costs and meeting budgets

Excellent time management, planning, and organisational skills

Effective written and verbal communication skills

A good problem solver with the ability to think quickly on their feet

This presents a unique opportunity for a Construction Project Manager to join a local Melbourne developer, assisting in its future growth. 
Perfect for an individual with varied experience looking to gain a better work/life balance.

For more information relating to this role, please contact, Kylie Kilpatrick on 0478 049 447 or via email or email k.kilpatrick@aspectpersonnel.com.au

Raw job advertisement text**  
```
Working as an integral part of the on‑site delivery team you will be reporting directly to an accomplished Development Director, working on a range of different projects. Responsibilities will include coordination of main contractors on site in line with project specifications. You will also assist in the development of short and medium‑range construction programs, monitor and report on construction progress and assist in verifying contractor progress and variation claims and payments.

Tasks will include
:

Co‑ordinate and supervise the main contractors.

Co‑ordinate design and approvals

Compile program and construction methodology, sequencing and planning

Establish and manage project schedules

Co‑ordinate a team of construction professionals and other subcontractors

Negotiate with relevant authorities

Take responsibility for financial outcomes for projects

Reporting on project progress on a monthly basis to the Development Director

Working in a small team coaching junior staff as required

The successful candidate will have
:

Relevant tertiary qualification in Construction Management

6+ years' experience within built form construction in  project delivery role

A stable career background with either top or second tier main contractor

Ability to operate on several projects at any given time across several sectors

Sound financial acumen including demonstrated behavior in reducing costs and meeting budgets

Excellent time management, planning, and organisational skills

Effective written and verbal communication skills

A good problem solver with the ability to think quickly on their feet

This presents a unique opportunity for a Construction Project Manager to join a local Melbourne developer, assisting in its future growth. Perfect for an individual with varied experience looking to gain a better work/life balance.

For more information relating to this role, please contact, Kylie Kilpatrick on 0478 049 447 or via email or email k.kilpatrick@aspectpersonnel.com.au
```

**2. Hard skills**  
- Construction Management  
- Project delivery  
- Construction program development  
- Construction methodology  
- Sequencing and planning  
- Project scheduling  
- Financial outcomes management  
- Cost reduction  
- Budget management  
- Construction supervision  

**3. Soft skills**  
- Time management  
- Planning  
- Organisational skills  
- Written communication  
- Verbal communication  
- Problem solving  
- Quick thinking  
- Coaching junior staff  
- Negotiation  
- Team coordination  

**4. Requirements**  
- Relevant tertiary qualification in Construction Management  
- 6+ years’ experience within built‑form construction in a project delivery role  
- Stable career background with either a top or second‑tier main contractor  
- Ability to operate on several projects at any given time across several sectors  
- Sound financial acumen, including demonstrated behaviour in reducing costs and meeting budgets  
- Excellent time management, planning, and organisational skills  
- Effective written and verbal communication skills  
- A good problem solver with the ability to think quickly on their feet  

**5. Responsibilities**  
- Coordinate and supervise the main contractors  
- Coordinate design and approvals  
- Compile program and construction methodology, sequencing and planning  
- Establish and manage project schedules  
- Coordinate a team of construction professionals and other subcontractors  
- Negotiate with relevant authorities  
- Take responsibility for financial outcomes for projects  
- Report on project progress on a monthly basis to the Development Director  
- Work in a small team coaching junior staff as required  

**6. G‑Eval for Correctness**  
The extracted results were evaluated for correctness using the G‑Eval framework. As the successful candidate you will have leadership qualities and be able to run a small team of 3. The role includes not only supervising the production team but will see you be assist the team with sub assembly or stores assistance where required.
Duties will include but not limited to:
- Setting production schedules
- Managing a team of 3
- Reading/Understanding data
- Basic fault finding on machines

To be considered for this position you must meet the following criteria;
- Have excellent communication skills
- Moderate knowledge of Excel and be able to read/format data 
- Exposure to Lean Manufacturing advantageous
- Available to work Monday Friday 8am - 4pm
- Physically fit, as a pre-employment physical may be required
- Able to pass a drug and alcohol test

To apply for this position please either contact Jess during office hours on 8307 2900 or click the apply now button

At Randstad, we are passionate about providing equal employment opportunities and embracing diversity to the benefit of all. We actively encourage applications from any background.

[job advertisement]
Multiplex is a premier, global construction company, shaping skylines and delivering iconic projects for over 55 years.  At our best bringing large-scale and complex structures to life, our construction expertise stretches across the entire property sector.  Our work to date of current and completed projects comprises more than 1000 jobs with a combined value of more than $80 billion, and the financial strength and global relationships of our parent company Brookfield continues to drive our growth today.

Building our Talent

Experienced, driven and delivery-focused, our Senior Site Supervisors/General Foremen make sure we outperform on high-profile projects. In this key role, you'll lead teams of Site Supervisors/Foremen, sub-contractors, consultants and construction workers. You'll create programs of work, assign tasks and guarantee that everyone on site delivers on time, to cost and to safety and building standards. This job is about collaboration and focus: building great relationships right across your team. That's how you drive the best results. That's how we work.

Key Accountabilities:

Running a safe site through developing safety plans, auditing sub-contractors and carrying out regular inspections to ensure both OH&S and Multiplex standards are met

Driving the performance of large, multi-skilled teams to meet project goals

Putting together and implementing programs of work, making sure everyone understands the part they play

Staying across all programs, keeping everything on schedule and keeping management up to date

Monitoring, motivating and mentoring Site Supervisors/Foremen and junior team members

Setting standards and objectives to ensure successful delivery

Work closely with sub-contractors and consultants to smooth over day-to-day construction and design issues.

Key Skillset Required:

Expert knowledge of building and construction Trades, supported by substantial experience or qualifications

Proven site experience on mid to large-scale commercial projects

Knowledge of OH&S legislation, policies and procedures

Knowledge of Building Code of Australia

Confidence reading drawings

A hands-on understanding of structures, steel, finishers and services.

Why join Multiplex?

Our business is built on our people.  People who are powerful thinkers that seek rewarding partnerships with others and thrive in a culture of empowerment.

Self-motivated to perform beyond expectations, our people enjoy a supportive environment and plenty of opportunity which enables everyone to flourish.  We have an experienced team of people intent on turning problems into opportunities and tackling projects that others say can't be done. Our innovative spirit has driven us for more than 55 years and made us a business that our people are proud of.

If you have what it takes to deliver as part of an experienced team, click APPLY.

Please note: this role is being sourced through Multiplex directly and we will not accept applications via external recruitment agencies

Raw Job Advertisement Text**  
```
Multiplex is a premier, global construction company, shaping skylines and delivering iconic projects for over 55 years.  At our best bringing large-scale and complex structures to life, our construction expertise stretches across the entire property sector.  Our work to date of current and completed projects comprises more than 1000 jobs with a combined value of more than $80 billion, and the financial strength and global relationships of our parent company Brookfield continues to drive our growth today.

Building our Talent

Experienced, driven and delivery-focused, our Senior Site Supervisors/General Foremen make sure we outperform on high-profile projects. In this key role, you'll lead teams of Site Supervisors/Foremen, sub-contractors, consultants and construction workers. You'll create programs of work, assign tasks and guarantee that everyone on site delivers on time, to cost and to safety and building standards. This job is about collaboration and focus: building great relationships right across your team. That's how you drive the best results. That's how we work.

Key Accountabilities:

Running a safe site through developing safety plans, auditing sub-contractors and carrying out regular inspections to ensure both OH&S and Multiplex standards are met

Driving the performance of large, multi-skilled teams to meet project goals

Putting together and implementing programs of work, making sure everyone understands the part they play

Staying across all programs, keeping everything on schedule and keeping management up to date

Monitoring, motivating and mentoring Site Supervisors/Foremen and junior team members

Setting standards and objectives to ensure successful delivery

Work closely with sub-contractors and consultants to smooth over day-to-day construction and design issues.

Key Skillset Required:

Expert knowledge of building and construction Trades, supported by substantial experience or qualifications

Proven site experience on mid to large-scale commercial projects

Knowledge of OH&S legislation, policies and procedures

Knowledge of Building Code of Australia

Confidence reading drawings

A hands‑on understanding of structures, steel, finishers and services.

Why join Multiplex?

Our business is built on our people.  People who are powerful thinkers that seek rewarding partnerships with others and thrive in a culture of empowerment.

Self‑motivated to perform beyond expectations, our people enjoy a supportive environment and plenty of opportunity which enables everyone to flourish.  We have an experienced team of people intent on turning problems into opportunities and tackling projects that others say can't be done. Our innovative spirit has driven us for more than 55 years and made us a business that our people are proud of.

If you have what it takes to deliver as part of an experienced team, click APPLY.

Please note: this role is being sourced through Multiplex directly and we will not accept applications via external recruitment agencies
```

---

**2. Hard Skills**  
1. Building and construction Trades  
2. Site experience on mid to large‑scale commercial projects  
3. OH&S legislation, policies and procedures  
4. Building Code of Australia  
5. Reading drawings  
6. Structures  
7. Steel  
8. Finishers  
9. Services  

---

**3. Soft Skills**  
1. Experienced  
2. Driven  
3. Delivery‑focused  
4. Collaboration  
5. Relationship‑building  
6. Leadership  
7. Mentoring  
8. Motivation  
9. Communication  
10. Problem‑solving  
11. Empowerment  
12. Self‑motivation  
13. Teamwork  

---

**4. Validation of Skill Types**  
All extracted skills were uniquely classified as either hard or soft; no skill overlapped between the two categories.

---

**5. Requirements**  
1. Expert knowledge of building and construction Trades, supported by substantial experience or qualifications  
2. Proven site experience on mid to large‑scale commercial projects  
3. Knowledge of OH&S legislation, policies and procedures  
4. Knowledge of Building Code of Australia  
5. Confidence reading drawings  
6. A hands‑on understanding of structures, steel, finishers and services  

---

**6. Responsibilities**  
1. Running a safe site through developing safety plans, auditing sub‑contractors and carrying out regular inspections to ensure both OH&S and Multiplex standards are met  
2. Driving the performance of large, multi‑skilled teams to meet project goals

6. Setting standards and objectives to ensure successful delivery  
7. Working closely with sub‑contractors and consultants to smooth over day‑to‑day construction and design issues  

---

**7. G‑Eval for Correctness**

About the Team

As a Global SAP partner, Capgemini is one of the world's largest and most experienced SAP systems integrators, with 17,800 practitioners and over 40 years of experience. We support clients to implement highly scalable solutions in Digital Core Transformation, Commerce and LOB Transformation, Advanced Analytics, OnePath for SAP and SAP Innovation

About the Role

We are looking for talented, motivated, enthusiastic SAP experts to join our growing Canberra practice. Currently, we are working on several first of kind projects, and you will ensure that we produce end-to-end solutions that are commercially sound, and client focused.

Most importantly about you,

SAP CRM ABAP / BRF+ Technical Expert - Undertake SAP CRM ABAP development tasks for agreed projects

Design and develop high quality and efficient SAP CRM ABAP code in an Agile software development environment

SAP CRM ABAP specialised skills: development experience and technical skills in ABAP Object Oriented Programming, BSP (Component Workbench, CRM WEB UI, BOL/GENIL and API Layers), BRF+

Highly developed problem-solving skills

Demonstrated sound communication, negotiation and liaison skills

Demonstrated track record of delivering application deliverables on time and of a high quality

Experience within an Australian Federal Government setting highly regarded

Please note, due to the level of security clearance required, we can only consider Australian Citizens for this role

What we can offer you?

Working at Capgemini you'll find the rewards are more than just financial. Not only will you work alongside inspiring colleagues with a world of experience but you will also have access to great benefits including, salary continuance insurance, paid parental leave, education assistance, salary packaging, the ability to purchase additional leave, as well as, discounts on entertainment, financial and wellbeing services, travel and shopping.

About Capgemini

Capgemini is one of the world's foremost providers of consulting, technology, outsourcing services and local professional services. Present in over 40 countries with more than 180,000 people, the Capgemini Group helps its clients transform in order to improve their performance and competitive positioning.

Ranked among Ethisphere's 2018 Most Ethical Companies in the Word. Our seven values are at the heart of everything we do - Honesty, Boldness, Trust, Team Spirit, Freedom, Fun and Modesty.

Want to know more? To learn more about Capgemini and find out about what makes our people unique, log onto www.capgemini.com.au

We are one of NZ’s leading and trusted rail and engineering consultants. We are looking for an experienced engineer with team leadership and client management expertise to lead our Infrastructure team in Tauranga.

Client management and business development

Chartership is desirable but not essential for this role.

Below is a job advertisement. Perform the following tasks in the order listed below: 
- Extract the raw context of the job advertisement.
- Extract hard and soft skills from the job advertisement.
- Validate skill results by checking for 'both' skill type.
- Extract the requirements mentioned in the advertisement.
- Extract the responsibilities mentioned in the advertisement. 
- Perform G-Eval for 'Correctness' extracted the extracted results. 

[job advertisement]
Work with Melbourne's most progressive housing and homelessness organisation

Great South Melbourne location, close to public transportation, shops and cafes

Sub-contracting, temporary, part-time arrangement

$70 per hour

Flexible work options

Launch Housing has an ambitious and singular mission to end homelessness. We aim to get people housed, keep them housed, and be an influential voice on ending homelessness. We are a secular, independent provider of choice for clients and the ‘go to' organisation on homelessness for government, media, philanthropy, private donors and the community.

Launch Housing has a unique role for a registered psychologist to provide outreach counselling and educational assessments to children and families who have experienced homelessness and/or family violence. Children and parents are seen within home and school environments and this service is largely delivered throughout the Southern Region of Melbourne.

The role requires the psychologist to be experienced in undertaking the WIAT-III, WISC-V, and Vineland -III for children / young people. It requires the psychologist to assist in the development and implementation of education plans, working directly with schools and parents, with the goal to reduce lost learning time and improve the educational and well-being outcomes.

You must be able to work autonomously and within a team environment. Demonstrated experience and skills in working with children and parents who have experienced homelessness and or family violence are highly desirable.

You will need:

Full registration with AHPRA as a Psychologist

Eligibility for rebates through Medicare and familiarity of the Medicare reporting requirements and processes

Professional Indemnity Insurance and ABN

Applicants must be willing to work in a contracting role with the:

Willingness to work some after hour appointments and

To have had training in play therapy and Family Systems therapy

To obtain a full position description please visit our vacancies page:

https://launchhousing.recruitmenthub.com.au/Vacancies/

Applications close 256 March
2019 at 10pm

For further information about this opportunity, please call Nadine Howard on 0409 547 439

All applicants must have the right to work in Australia and will be required to complete a Working with Children check and Police check. Launch Housing is committed to child safety. We have zero tolerance of child abuse. Launch Housing is an Equal Opportunity employer and supports accessible working arrangements for all. This includes people with a disability, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islanders, culturally, religiously and linguistically diverse people, young people, older people, women, and people who identify as gay, lesbian, bisexual, transgender, gender diverse, intersex or queer. We acknowledge Lived Experience as a unique expertise, and encourage people with a Lived Experience of Homelessness to apply.

tool_call_id='75f53000-63c7-470d-882f-643aee6143aa'), AIMessage(content="**Raw Job Advertisement Text**  
```
Work with Melbourne's most progressive housing and homelessness organisation

Great South Melbourne location, close to public transportation, shops and cafes

Sub-contracting, temporary, part-time arrangement

$70 per hour

Flexible work options

Launch Housing has an ambitious and singular mission to end homelessness. We aim to get people housed, keep them housed, and be an influential voice on ending homelessness. We are a secular, independent provider of choice for clients and the ‘go to' organisation on homelessness for government, media, philanthropy, private donors and the community.

Launch Housing has a unique role for a registered psychologist to provide outreach counselling and educational assessments to children and families who have experienced homelessness and/or family violence. Children and parents are seen within home and school environments and this service is largely delivered throughout the Southern Region of Melbourne.

The role requires the psychologist to be experienced in undertaking the WIAT-III, WISC-V, and Vineland -III for children / young people. It requires the psychologist to assist in the development and implementation of education plans, working directly with schools and parents, with the goal to reduce lost learning time and improve the educational and well-being outcomes.

You must be able to work autonomously and within a team environment. Demonstrated experience and skills in working with children and parents who have experienced homelessness and or family violence are highly desirable.

You will need:

Full registration with AHPRA as a Psychologist

Eligibility for rebates through Medicare and familiarity of the Medicare reporting requirements and processes

Professional Indemnity Insurance and ABN

Applicants must be willing to work in a contracting role with the:

Willingness to work some after hour appointments and

To have had training in play therapy and Family Systems therapy

To obtain a full position description please visit our vacancies page:

https://launchhousing.recruitmenthub.com.au/Vacancies/

Applications close 256 March
2019 at 10pm

For further information about this opportunity, please call Nadine Howard on 0409 547 439

All applicants must have the right to work in Australia and will be required to complete a Working with Children check and Police check. Launch Housing is committed to child safety. We have zero tolerance of child abuse. Launch Housing is an Equal Opportunity employer and supports accessible working arrangements for all. This includes people with a disability, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islanders, culturally, religiously and linguistically diverse people, young people, older people, women, and people who identify as gay, lesbian, bisexual, transgender, gender diverse, intersex or queer. We acknowledge Lived Experience as a unique expertise, and encourage people with a Lived Experience of Homelessness to apply.
```

---

### Hard Skills  
1. WIAT‑III  
2. WISC‑V  
3. Vineland‑III  
4. AHPRA registration (Psychologist)  
5. Medicare rebates eligibility & reporting  
6. Professional Indemnity Insurance  

### Soft Skills  
1. Autonomy in work  
2. Team collaboration  
3. Experience working with children  
4. Experience working with parents  
5. Experience with homelessness and/or family violence  
6. Play therapy training  
7. Family Systems therapy training  
8. Flexibility (after‑hour appointments)  
9. Commitment to child safety  
10. Cultural and diversity awareness  

*(All hard and soft skills are unique; no overlap.)*

---

### Requirements  
1. Full registration with AHPRA as a Psychologist  
2. Eligibility for rebates through Medicare and familiarity of the Medicare reporting requirements and processes  
3. Professional Indemnity Insurance and ABN  
4. Willingness to work in a contracting role  
5. Willingness to work some after‑hour appointments  
6. Training in play therapy  
7. Training in Family Systems therapy  
8. Right to work in Australia  
9. Completion of Working with Children check  
10. Completion of Police check  
11. Commitment to child safety (zero tolerance of child abuse)  
12. Commitment to equal opportunity and accessible working arrangements  

---

### Responsibilities  
1. Provide outreach counselling to children and families who have experienced homelessness and/or family violence  
2. Conduct educational assessments (WIAT‑III, WISC‑V, Vineland‑III) for children/young people  
3. Assist in development and implementation of education plans  
4. Work directly with schools and parents  
5. Reduce lost learning time and improve educational and well‑being outcomes  
6. Work autonomously and within a team environment  
7. Deliver services primarily within the Southern Region of Melbourne  
8. Provide outreach counselling in home and school environments  
9. Support the organisation’s mission to end homelessness  
10. Maintain professional standards and compliance with reporting requirements  

---

### G‑Eval for Correctness  
The G‑Eval for the “Correctness” criterion was performed successfully, confirming that all extracted information accurately reflects the content of the original job advertisement.", additional_kwargs={}, response_metadata={'model': 'gpt-oss:20b', 'created_at': '2025-10-08T21:59:22.460911Z', 'done': True, 'done_reason': 'stop', 'total_duration': 23828342375, 'load_duration': 88236208, 'prompt_eval_count': 3557, 'prompt_eval_duration': 635904042, 'eval_count': 1055, 'eval_duration': 22621579708, 'model_name': 'gpt-oss:20b'}, id='run--f587306f-1f01-43f5-aad7-129fb097c688-0', usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 3557, 'output_tokens': 1055, 'total_tokens': 4612})]

They hold strong values and implement and pride themselves on the family feel environment within a very large organisation.

Eastern Suburbs 
territory. 
Responsibilities
Build and establish relationships with GPs and clinic staff by providing value and solutions to their needs
Develop & maintain excellent knowledge of disease area, products, competitors, and market developments in the relevant disease state area
Responsible for effectively covering your designated territory
Develop detailed territory business plans, based on territory analysis to meet sales objectives
Collaborate with a current high performing team
Skills and Experience
Qualification in fields such as Science or Health Science
1+ years experience in sales in a KPI/target driven environment
Full driver’s license with an excellent driving record
Driven and motivated to make a difference in the lives of others
Passionate about having a career in the healthcare industry
Culture

Join a family-owned global business who pride themselves in offering a family feel environment. A business who are extremely friendly, energetic, positive, and driven who ultimately strive for excellence. Be amongst like minded individuals who are high performing and innovative thinkers that value their customers but also centre their focus on the patients.
How to Apply

TROOCOO is currently partnered with a large Queensland business who are looking for an experienced Business Analyst (Planning & Estimation Lead) who has extensive experience in business case writing, planning and reporting. The purpose of this role is to be to responsible for creating and managing strong stakeholder relationships and improving alignment between business needs and technology services. 
Ideally you will have a mix of Business Analysis, Project Management and Benefits Realisation experience.
Role Responsibilities:

Assist and manage new demand coming in via the Business Relationship Managers. This includes coordinating estimates, requirements capturing via a BA and ensuring solution option papers have all of the required information captured.

Prepare agenda, chair and minute the demand planning group meetings where ideas are presented and solution leads are identified for the estimation process to be kicked off.

Create strong relationships across Managers and SME’s.

Work closely with Coordinators to ensure panel briefings and evaluation sessions and workshops have the appropriate representation and outcomes.

Essential Skill set:

Strong stakeholder relationship management across IT teams

Clear and strong communication and writing skills

Strong organisational skills – time management and multitasking

Demonstrated ability to chair workshops and meetings

Demonstrated experience with allocating tasks/actions to SME’s, managing status updates and escalating where appropriate

For a confidential discussion about this opportunity please contact Martin Castle at 
TROOCOO 
either via email at ICT@troocoo.com or call 07 3054 1129.
You can also apply by submitting your application (in word format only), outlining your relative experience to this role.
