TROOCOO is currently partnered with a large Queensland business who are looking for an experienced Business Analyst (Planning & Estimation Lead) who has extensive experience in business case writing, planning and reporting. The purpose of this role is to be to responsible for creating and managing strong stakeholder relationships and improving alignment between business needs and technology services. 
Ideally you will have a mix of Business Analysis, Project Management and Benefits Realisation experience.
Role Responsibilities:

Assist and manage new demand coming in via the Business Relationship Managers. This includes coordinating estimates, requirements capturing via a BA and ensuring solution option papers have all of the required information captured.

Prepare agenda, chair and minute the demand planning group meetings where ideas are presented and solution leads are identified for the estimation process to be kicked off.

Create strong relationships across Managers and SME’s.

Work closely with Coordinators to ensure panel briefings and evaluation sessions and workshops have the appropriate representation and outcomes.

Essential Skill set:

Strong stakeholder relationship management across IT teams

Clear and strong communication and writing skills

Strong organisational skills – time management and multitasking

Demonstrated ability to chair workshops and meetings

Demonstrated experience with allocating tasks/actions to SME’s, managing status updates and escalating where appropriate

For a confidential discussion about this opportunity please contact Martin Castle at 
TROOCOO 
either via email at ICT@troocoo.com or call 07 3054 1129.
You can also apply by submitting your application (in word format only), outlining your relative experience to this role.
```

---

### Hard Skills  
1. Business case writing  
2. Planning  
3. Reporting  
4. Business Analysis  
5. Project Management  
6. Benefits Realisation  
7. Estimating  
8. Requirements capturing  

### Soft Skills  
1. Stakeholder relationship management  
2. Communication (clear & strong)  
3. Writing skills  
4. Organisational skills (time management, multitasking)  
5. Workshop facilitation (chairing)  
6. Meeting facilitation (chairing)  
7. Task allocation  
8. Status management  
9. Escalation  

### Validation of Skill Types  
All extracted skills are unique and correctly classified as either hard or soft; no overlap was found.

---

### Requirements  
1. Extensive experience in business case writing, planning and reporting.  
2. Experience in business analysis, project management and benefits realisation.  
3. Ability to create and manage strong stakeholder relationships.  
4. Ability to improve alignment between business needs and technology services.  
5. Ability to coordinate estimates and capture requirements via a BA.  
6. Ability to prepare agendas, chair and minute demand planning group meetings.  
7. Ability to identify solution leads for the estimation process.  
8. Ability to create strong relationships across managers and SMEs.  
9. Ability to work closely with coordinators to ensure panel briefings, evaluation sessions and workshops have appropriate representation and outcomes.  
10. Demonstrated ability to chair workshops and meetings.  
11. Demonstrated experience with allocating tasks/actions to SMEs, managing status updates and escalating where appropriate.  
12. Contact details for confidential discussion (Martin Castle, email ICT@troocoo.com, phone 07 3054 1129).  

---

### Responsibilities  
1. Assist and manage new demand coming in via the Business Relationship Managers, coordinating estimates, capturing requirements via a BA, and ensuring solution option papers contain all required information.  
2. Prepare agenda, chair and minute the demand planning group meetings where ideas are presented and solution leads are identified for the estimation process to be kicked off.  
3. Create strong relationships across managers and SMEs.  
4. Work closely with coordinators to ensure panel briefings, evaluation sessions and workshops have the appropriate representation and outcomes.  

---

Contract administration

Replacement cost analysis prior to site investigations

About the company

Regis is an industry leading, national aged care provider that offers a range of care and support services to suit the individual needs of senior Australians. We are proud of our 20 years of experience in aged care, and of the 8000 passionate people who are devoted to providing person-centred support to every individual in our care.

Workplace Location

Regis Norwood is a warm and welcoming community on a quiet street between the Punchbowl Reserve and the North Esk River. It is a place dedicated to providing quality aged care for people who want to live life on their terms.

A 94 rooms facility, Regis Norwood provides the full range of Regis aged care services, plus ageing-in-place, a specialist dementia care wing and respite care services.

About the role

The role of the Clinical Manager is to lead and manage the clinical, allied health, therapy and lifestyle services. This will enable specific care and service objectives to be met and will ensure that high standard of person centred care is provided to all residents within all legislative and professional standards requirements.

Duties & Responsibilities

Full clinical oversight of the facility

All clinical reporting and documentation

Staff training, provision of ongoing management and support to all care staff

Oversight of all specialised nursing

Working closely with the Facility Manager and leadership team to ensure consistent compliance with all Aged Care standards and Regis Quality Care policies and procedures

Ensuring all staff adhere to safe practices and follow all WHS requirements

Ideal Skill & Experience

Qualified Registered Nurse with current AHPRA registration

Minimum 12 months experience as a Clinical Manager

A hands on approach to your role with a focus on customer service and leadership

Strong IT skills including previous experience using a care management system

A robust approach to managing your time effectively and ability to work within deadlines

Workplace Culture

Regis is more than a great company to work for, it’s a way of life that offers genuine opportunities for people to expand their horizons and realise their potential. Our size, reputation and growth ensures every employee has ready access to financial, professional development, recognition and wellbeing benefits that are second to none.

Employee Benefits

As a Clinical Manager, you are welcomed into Regis by participating in a structured and thorough on boarding program which runs for 4 weeks. The benefit of such a program is the ability to learn your role in a new company and settling in before taking the reigns of the job.

We provide the opportunity for everyone within Regis to reach their career goals – for our Clinical Managers this is facilitated through an on going tailored and individual development plan that you will create with your Manager.

Additional benefits include-

Monthly state based clinical leadership meetings

An individual development plan tailored to your unique skills and goals

Support from a dedicated state-based clinical support team

For a career that’s more than just a job, apply now!

1. Use write_todos to create a TODO at the start of the user's request, per the tool description.
2. Update the todos key in the ReActConversationState state. 
3. When you accomplish a TODO, use read_todos to read the TODOs in order to remind yourself of the plan.
4. Reflect on what you've done and the TODO.
5. Mark your task as completed, and proceed to the next TODO item.
6. Continue this process until you have completed all the TODO items created.", additional_kwargs={}, response_metadata={}, id='7b5ac708-ee19-4a3d-a15d-60886bebd778'), HumanMessage(content="
Below is a job advertisement. Perform the following tasks in the order listed below: 
- Extract the raw context of the job advertisement.
- Extract hard and soft skills from the job advertisement.
- Validate skill results by checking for 'both' skill type.
- Extract the requirements mentioned in the advertisement.
- Extract the responsibilities mentioned in the advertisement. 
- Perform G-Eval for 'Correctness' extracted the extracted results. 

[job advertisement]
Diona is an award-winning business with a portfolio of high-profile projects built on a solid reputation and more than 38 years’ experience.  We are specialists in the design and construction of cable laying installations, water, sewer and gas pipelines, as well as drainage and concrete construction. Our services encompass every aspect of utility infrastructure design and construction.

We have a long-term pipeline of projects across Sydney and we are growing! We have a number of exciting opportunities available for ambitious and driven Site Engineers & Project Engineers who are looking to take the next step in their careers.  Our head office is based in Rouse Hill but a majority of our project sites are based in and around Sydney CBD.

Day to day you will report to the Project Manager and provide planning, technical advice and management of various project activities ensuring key project deliverables are met. You will work alongside a strong and passionate team to deliver exceptional outcomes for our clients.

To be successful you will be a degree qualified Engineer with 3+ years’ experience delivering underground utilities and services projects (water & sewer, electricity and/or gas). You will be passionate about what you do and have the ability to lead and motivate your team to deliver quality results. You will also have a strong commitment to safety, which is always our first priority.

As our most valuable asset, we invest in our employees’ personal and professional growth. We provide a range of benefits, including ongoing professional development, on the job training, study support, leadership and management programs, competitive remuneration packages, generous employee referral incentives and a host of health and wellbeing benefits to help you thrive in our team.

If you are looking for your next challenge 
APPLY NOW
or contact Ciaran McGreevy on 02 8405 1575 for a confidential discussion.

Below is a job advertisement. Perform the following tasks in the order listed below: 
- Extract the raw context of the job advertisement.
- Extract hard and soft skills from the job advertisement.

- Extract the requirements mentioned in the advertisement.

[job advertisement]
Who are we?

Olympus Solutions is the Employment Services division of Ability Options and are a leading provider of Employment Services in the greater Sydney Metropolitan area, Central Coast, Hunter and Wollongong regions.

With 33 offices across NSW, each month we place more than 300 people into jobs. Our success is due to the large range of no cost employment services we provide businesses, along our passion to enhance people's lives through employment. 
Olympus Solutions hold the contracts with the Government and Ability Options is responsible for the sites, the employers and the job seekers that come through jobactive, DES, ParentsNext and VTEC. 
The Role

Supporting people in the Baulkham Hills area, you will be working with a diverse range of people living with disability and employer networks to secure employment opportunities for participants wanting to achieve their employment aspirations.
As an Employer Engagement Consultant you will be direct marketing to employers on behalf of a candidates that do not have the capability themselves, offering financial and other creative incentives to ensure a smooth handover process of a newly found or carved position.
You will advocate on the behalf of others by providing training and advice to employers and organisations around implementing a productive workplace for people with a disability including workplace modifications.
About You
You will be passionate about enhancing customer experience and motivated to succeed with a proven track record in meeting KPIs, building relationships and displaying a resilient can do attitude.
To succeed in this role you will need to be able to demonstrate:

Your proven track record in meeting KPIs in a sales driven industry or employment services industry

Your capability of meeting performance targets and aptitude to think on your feet

Your proven ability to problem solve effectively and showcase excellent time management skills

Your knowledge of the local labour market and employment opportunities

Your excellent administration skills and ability to maintain thorough case notes

Your excellent communication skills to be able to promote job seekers to local employers and to seek future employment opportunities
Essential Criteria

Current driver's licence

Working With Children's Check (or willingness to obtain)

Experience in sales-focused roles and/or

Experience in Employment Services

Own vehicle with Comprehensive Car Insurance        
This role attracts a $10,000 car allowance as it requires travel.
Why Work for Us?
Our innovative service delivery model is driven by our commitment to ensure all people have the right support to find a job they love that makes a meaningful contribution to their community.
Olympus Solutions | Ability Options is committed to a workplace culture that recognizes diversity, equity and human rights. We respect and value the contribution of people from all cultures, backgrounds and lifestyles.

Ability Options is a White Ribbon accredited workplace.

To apply online, please click on the appropriate link.

[{'ad_text': 'Up to $110k including super plus performance based incentives

Macquarie Park - Parking provided | Globally listed organisation

Busy and dynamic position | Utilise your demand planning skills

Our client is listed on the international stock exchange and is a subsidiary of the world’s largest provider of crop services. They are experts in the production of sustainable crops and farming including marketing livestock and wool, finance services, real estate and much more.
They are seeking a Demand Planner to join their Operations team with a focus on Inventory Management, Demand Planning and Order Management. The position is based in Macquarie Park and reports directly to the Divisional General Manager.
The ideal candidate will be excited by the prospect of working within a cohesive team, with the ability to build relationships with internal and external stakeholders and places priority on delivery of exceptional Customer Service.

Primarily, this position will be responsible for:

Building and maintaining effective relationships with Product Managers and Suppliers

Reporting on stock levels and replenishing using historical data, ensuring ideal stock levels

Contributing to improvement projects and reviewing processes

Managing orders by validating and ensuring planning is in place to meet key performance indicators

Tracking orders and investigation of any discrepancies, intervening to make sure there is minimal impact to delivery times

Consistently reviewing processes to improve stock levels and reduce delivery times

General adhoc duties as required

The successful applicants will possess majority of the following attributes:

5 years + experience working within Demand, Forecasting and Supply Planning, preferably for an Agricultural organisation

Demonstrated ability to build relationships with key stakeholders, able to negotiate, provide advice and influence

You will be able to work autonomously and have outstanding organisational skills, but also able to collaborate in a tight knit team

Technically minded, can adapt to new systems and programs, particularly have used SAP in previous positions or had exposure to

Excellent problem-solving abilities takes initiative and enjoys a challenge. You will be able to think outside the box and encourage others to do the same

Tertiary Qualifications in Supply Chain would be advantageous

If you are ticking all the boxes with your skills and experience and have a strong desire and passion to contribute to the future of the farming sector, please submit your resume via the “apply now” button. Only suitable applicants will be contacted.'}]

6. Continue this process until you have completed all the TODO items created.", additional_kwargs={}, response_metadata={}, id='e2e8e217-7210-4b64-804c-2504fb8d9fb1'), HumanMessage(content="
Below is a job advertisement. Perform the following tasks in the order listed below: 
- Extract the raw context of the job advertisement.
- Extract hard and soft skills from the job advertisement.
- Validate skill results by checking for 'both' skill type.
- Extract the requirements mentioned in the advertisement.
- Extract the responsibilities mentioned in the advertisement. 
- Perform G-Eval for 'Correctness' extracted the extracted results. 

[job advertisement]
Home care Quality Manager job working within a large-scale not for profit healthcare organisation based in VIC

Your new company
This large-scale Not-for-Profit organisation works to provide a variety of healthcare services, including but not limited to hospital care, aged care, palliative care, home and community care, and mental health programs. This role sits within the Home Care division, with offices across Victoria and interstate.

Your new role
Reporting through to the Executive Director of Quality, Safety, and Innovation, you will be charged with, but certainly not limited to:
Overseeing the Quality Management Framework within the Home Care Services of the organisation.
Chairing the Quality and Risk Committee and will sit within the divisions leadership group of the division
Engaging with Senior Management and relevant Business Partners to formulate and implement a strategic approach to quality management and improvement for the Home Care division
You will ensure all compliance with quality aspects of finding and service agreements is adhered to
Monitoring and reporting on relevant industry and legislative changes and will advise on potential impacts and risks
Leadership of the preparation of third-party audits and reviews, conducting second party auditing of sub-contractors and assisting the business with applications to tenders.
What you'll need to succeed
To succeed in this role, you will have:
Proven success in a Quality Management role within an aged care, home service, or clinical setting
Deep understanding of relevant accreditation within the aged care and health care sectors
Experience in chairing senior management committees
Impeccable stakeholder engagement and management capabilities, with the ability to communicate with a senior executive level audience
Previous experience managing a small team will be highly advantageous
What you'll get in return
A chance to be a part of a truly fantastic organisation with fantastic offices in Richmond. You will have the ability to influence organisation wide strategic plans, while working alongside Senior Executives within the business.

What you need to do now
If you're interested in this role, click 'apply now' to forward an up-to-date copy of your CV, or call Oliver Attkins on 0396049645 for further information.
If this job isn't quite right for you but you are looking for a new position, please contact us for a confidential discussion on your career.

Home care Quality Manager job working within a large-scale not for profit healthcare organisation based in VIC

Your new company
This large-scale Not-for-Profit organisation works to provide a variety of healthcare services, including but not limited to hospital care, aged care, palliative care, home and community care, and mental health programs. This role sits within the Home Care division, with offices across Victoria and interstate.

Your new role
Reporting through to the Executive Director of Quality, Safety, and Innovation, you will be charged with, but certainly not limited to:
Overseeing the Quality Management Framework within the Home Care Services of the organisation.
Chairing the Quality and Risk Committee and will sit within the divisions leadership group of the division
Engaging with Senior Management and relevant Business Partners to formulate and implement a strategic approach to quality management and improvement for the Home Care division
You will ensure all compliance with quality aspects of finding and service agreements is adhered to
Monitoring and reporting on relevant industry and legislative changes and will advise on potential impacts and risks
Leadership of the preparation of third-party audits and reviews, conducting second party auditing of sub-contractors and assisting the business with applications to tenders.

What you'll need to succeed
To succeed in this role, you will have:
Proven success in a Quality Management role within an aged care, home service, or clinical setting
Deep understanding of relevant accreditation within the aged care and health care sectors
Experience in chairing senior management committees
Impeccable stakeholder engagement and management capabilities, with the ability to communicate with a senior executive level audience
Previous experience managing a small team will be highly advantageous

What you'll get in return
A chance to be a part of a truly fantastic organisation with fantastic offices in Richmond. You will have the ability to influence organisation wide strategic plans, while working alongside Senior Executives within the business.

What you need to do now
If you're interested in this role, click 'apply now' to forward an up-to-date copy of your CV, or call Oliver Attkins on 0396049645 for further information.
If this job isn't quite right for you but you are looking for a new position, please contact us for a confidential discussion on your career.
```

An opportunity to develop and grow your career within the business
